<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Velayati Leaves for Islamic Conference Talks in New York </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Velayati Leaves for Islamic Conference Talks in New York </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2604075794 Tehran IRNA in English 0608 GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2604075794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, April 26, IRNA -- Iran's Foreign Minister 
'Ali Akbar Velayati left here this morning for New York where he 
will take part in the ministerial meeting of the Organization of 
the Islamic Conference (OIC) contact group on 
Bosnia-Herzegovina. The contact group is to meet Wednesday at 
the United Nations headquarters upon Iran's proposal. 
  The foreign ministers of the OIC contact group will review 
the crisis in Bosnia-Herzegovina to explore ways to support the 
Bosnian Muslims. Malaysia, Pakistan, Senegal, Turkey, Saudi 
Arabia, Egypt, Tunisia, and Iran will take part in the meeting. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

