<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reza'i on Number of Iranian Pilgrims for Hajj </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reza'i on Number of Iranian Pilgrims for Hajj </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2504143094 Tehran IRNA in English 1405 GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2504143094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, April 25, IRNA -- Head of the Hajj and 
Pilgrimage Organization Hoseyn Reza'i on Monday did not confirm 
a BBC report that Saudi Arabia has agreed to the dispatch of 
115,000 Iranians to Mecca for this year's hajj pilgrimage. 
  Head of the organization, Mohammad Hoseyn Reza'i told IRNA 
here Monday that Iran has not yet received a formal agreement 
from the Riyadh government to the effect. 
  The Iranian official added that despite having little time 
Iran is ready to send at least 115,000 pilgrims to Saudi Arabia 
under an agreement signed by the Iranian and Saudi foreign 
ministers in Oman in 1990. Riyadh has cut Iran's quota to 
61,000. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

