<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Security Forces Arrest Students at Tehran Sit-In </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Security Forces Arrest Students at Tehran Sit-In </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2204145094 London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT in Arabic 22 Apr 94 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> PM2204145094 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Students Arrested in Iran"] </F>
  [Text] London, AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT -- Iranian universities 
have witnessed a number of sit-ins and protests staged by 
students over the past two days. Security forces have arrested 
a number of students accused of organizing the unrest. 
  Hundreds of students from Tehran University began a sit-in 
at 
the Faculty of Economics in northern Amirabad Street the day 
before yesterday. The sit-in continued until yesterday morning. 
A statement issued by the Iranian opposition movement 
"Mojahedin-e Khalq" said that "the mullahs' repressive forces 
have arrested a number of students in the belief that they are 
the organizers of the sit-in." 

</TEXT>

