<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Women Allowed To Be Advisers at Courts </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Women Allowed To Be Advisers at Courts </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2404104694 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 0930 GMT 24 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2404104694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] In today's open session of the Islamic 
Consultative Majles, the bill on reforming the conditions of 
choosing judges of the Ministry of Justice was approved. 
According to our correspondent, the bill provides for women who 
are eligible for appointment as judges of the Ministry of 
Justice and who have a judicial background to be employed as 
advisers at the administrative court of justice, the special 
civil courts, the public prosecutor's office, the investigations 
department, the office of legal studies, the legislative office 
of the Ministry of Justice [as heard], the office for the 
supervision of minors, the legal office, and other offices with 
judicial positions. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

