<H3> <TI>   Iraqi Speaker, Parliamentary Delegation Arrives </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Iraqi Speaker, Parliamentary Delegation Arrives </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Parliamentary Talks Begin </H4>

<F P=102> JN2504162394 Baghdad INA in English 1445 GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN2504162394 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Islamabad, Apr. 25, INA--The parliamentary talks 
between Pakistan and Iraq began here today. 
  The talks dealt with bilateral relations and means of 
boosting them and exchanging visits and expertise in the 
parliamentary fields. 
  Head of the Iraqi delegation, Speaker of the National 
Assembly Sa'di Mahdi Salih explained suffering of the Iraqi 
people as a result of the unjust blockade, despite Iraq's 
implementation of its commitments versus the Security Council 
resolutions. 
  For his part, Speaker of the Pakistani Parliament Yusuf Raza 
Gilani voiced his country's government and people concern over 
plight of the Iraqi people, criticizing the double-standard 
being pursued by the superpowers on the human rights and 
handling the international problems. 

</TEXT>

