<H3> <TI>   Iraqi Speaker, Parliamentary Delegation Arrives </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Iraqi Speaker, Parliamentary Delegation Arrives </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Senate Chairman Meets Speaker </H4>

<F P=102> BK2504154194 Islamabad PTV Television Network in English 
1400 GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2504154194 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad PTV Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Iraqi Speaker Mr. Sa'di Mahdi, met the chairman, 
Senate, Mr. Wasim Sajjad, in Islamabad today and discussed 
various issues, including Kashmir. The chairman, Senate, 
briefed Mr. Sa'di Mahdi Salih on the different aspects of the 
Kashmir issue and called for its peaceful solution through UN 
resolutions. Mr. Wasim Sajjad supported resumption of food and 
medicine supplies to Iraq and said these items should not be 
subjected to international sanctions. The Iraqi speaker 
expressed the hope that his current visit to Pakistan would 
further strengthen cooperation in trade, commerce, and economic 
sectors. 

</TEXT>

