<H3> <TI>   Iraqi Speaker, Parliamentary Delegation Arrives </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Iraqi Speaker, Parliamentary Delegation Arrives </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Bhutto Meets Delegation </H4>

<F P=102> BK2604054394 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in Urdu 0200 
GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2604054394 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Urdu </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The visiting four-member Iraqi delegation, led by 
National Assembly Speaker Sa'di Mahdi Salih, called on Prime 
Minister Ms. Benazir Bhutto in Islamabad yesterday. They 
exchanged views on matters of bilateral interest and regional 
and international issues. The Iraqi speaker commended the steps 
taken by the Pakistani prime minister for socioeconomic reforms. 
He hoped that the Islamic countries will end their differences 
and closely cooperate with each other for the welfare of their 
people. Ms. Benazir Bhutto paid tribute to the Iraqi people for 
facing the present difficulties with patience and hoped that 
Iraq will soon be able to overcome these difficulties. She said 
Pakistan has always supported the territorial integrity of all 
countries, and it will welcome normal relations among all 
Islamic countries. 

</TEXT>

