<H3> <TI>   Tibetan Youths Arrested Following Clashes </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Tibetan Youths Arrested Following Clashes </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2504141394 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0830 
GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2504141394 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In Himachal Pradesh, the situation in the Dharamsala 
town of Kangra District is peaceful. The town witnessed violent 
clashes following a stabbing incident on Saturday in which one 
person was killed and 15 injured. The state home secretary, Mr. 
S.N. Verma, told our Simla correspondent that the Tibetan youths 
believed to be involved in the incident have been arrested. 
Additional police reinforcements have been rushed to Dharamsala. 
The chief minister, Mr. Vir Bhadra Singh, has appealed to the 
people to exercise restraint and maintain communal amity. 

</TEXT>

