<F P=100> India </F>
<H3> <TI>   Conference Condemns Pakistan's Role in Kashmir </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Conference Condemns Pakistan's Role in Kashmir </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2404130094 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1230 
GMT 24 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2404130094 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The All India Urdu Editors and Intellectuals 
Conference has strongly condemned Pakistan's support to 
terrorism in Jammu and Kashmir. In a resolution in New Delhi 
today, the conference said while fighting militancy in the 
valley, it should be ensured that the lives of innocent people 
are protected. It suggested the government to send a delegation 
of Urdu editors to Kashmir to assess the situation there. The 
conference also stressed the need to review all TADA [Terrorism 
and Disruptive Activities Act] cases and demanded the release of 
innocent persons. 
  Addressing the conference the railway minister, C. K. Jaffar 
Shariff, said that efforts should be made to enlist people's 
support in restoring normalcy in Kashmir. The tourism and civil 
aviation minister, Mr. Ghulam Nabi Azad, warned Pakistan against 
meddling in India's internal affairs. He said Pakistani 
misadventures are only creating more problems for minorities 
rather than serving any purpose. 

</TEXT>

