GMT 24 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2404094594 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] India intends to restore preferential tariff margin 
on Sri Lankan clothes. The two-day meeting of the Indo-Sri 
Lankan Joint Commission held in New Delhi was told that this 
will be done as early as possible. An External Affairs Ministry 
press release said that both the countries decided to hold 
intergovernmental meetings on expansion of bilateral trade, as 
also the Sri Lankan request for increased market access for some 
of its products. Sri Lanka appreciated India's decision to 
extend a new line of credit to implement infrastructural 
development projects in that country. The two countries agreed 
in principle to collaborate in setting up an institute of 
technology and management in Sri Lanka. 

