<H3> <TI>   Foreign Investment Projects Signed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Investment Projects Signed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2304103594 Delhi Doordarshan Television Network in English 
1630 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2304103594 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi Doordarshan Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sixty-four projects with foreign investments of 
over $415 million were cleared during the five-day Investmart 
which concluded in New Delhi today. In addition, specific 
interests were shown in over 100 other projects. Giving details 
of the investments, the secretary, industrial development, Mr. 
Surender Singh, told newsmen that the largest investment of $152 
million was being made in the food processing sector followed by 
$142 million in metallurgy and $85 million dollars in the 
chemicals sector. While Italy led with the highest investment 
of $91 million, France signed the maximum number of 25 projects 
with Indian companies. Thirty two countries were represented at 
the Investmart which was organized jointly by the Industry 
Ministry and UNIDO [United Nations Industrial Development 
Organization]. Mr. Singh said that the government will be 
following up all the proposals for which letters of intent have 
been signed. 

</TEXT>

