<H3> <TI>   'Abbas Arrives in Cairo, Meets With Shahaq </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Abbas Arrives in Cairo, Meets With Shahaq </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2604094394 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0920 GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2604094394 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 26 Apr (MENA)--Mahmud 'Abbas, alias 
Abu-Mazin, a PLO Executive Committee member, arrived in Cairo 
this morning. He met General Amnon Shahaq, Israeli deputy chief 
of staff and head of the Israeli delegation to the 
Palestinian-Israeli negotiations. Palestinian sources said the 
meeting aims to bridge the gap between the two sides' views 
concerning various points that are still the subject of dispute, 
particularly the legal jurisdiction in Gaza and Jericho and the 
control of the crossings. 
  Abu-Mazin earlier met members of the Palestinian negotiating 
team. The talks during the meeting dealt with progress and the 
efforts required to coordinate the Palestinian stances on the 
proposals to be presented during this round of negotiations. 

</TEXT>

