<H3> <TI>   League Official on Libyan Call for Emergency Meeting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    League Official on Libyan Call for Emergency Meeting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2504135194 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1220 GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2504135194 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 25 Apr (MENA) -- An official source in the 
Arab League has stated that the League's Secretariat is awaiting 
the member states' response to the Libyan request to hold an 
emergency meeting of the foreign and defense ministers council. 
  The official explained that holding the meeting requires the 
consent of 12 Arab states. However, he added, if two states 
agree within 30 days of the request, the meeting will be held at 
the level of permanent delegates. 
  Libya called that extraordinary meeting to discuss the U.S. 
sophisticated weapons deal to Israel, in addition to other 
topics. 

