<H3> <TI>   Palestinian Manifesto Attacks PLO, 'Arafat </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Palestinian Manifesto Attacks PLO, 'Arafat </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2504143394 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1400 GMT 25 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2504143394 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A group of 23 Palestinian leaders from the 
territories, led by Haydar 'Abd-al-Shafi, today issued a 
manifesto expressing opposition to the concessions they say the 
PLO is making in the negotiations with Israel. The public 
statement says that any agreement which legitimizes Israel's 
unilateral and illegal actions in the territories -- such as the 
expropriation of lands, establishment of settlements, and the 
annexation of East Jerusalem -- will not bind the Palestinian 
people and its national institutions. 
  At a Jerusalem news conference, 'Abd-al-Shafi, who headed 
the 
Palestinian delegation to the negotiations with Israel, attacked 
the PLO and 'Arafat. He claimed that they are cut off from what 
is happening on the ground and that the Palestinian people will 
pay a heavy price for their mistakes. He also demanded 
democratization of the PLO and for the entire Palestinian people 
to be involved in deciding on the composition of its 
institutions. 
  Our correspondent Ron Nesi'el adds that among those who 
signed the manifesto are Ghassan al-Khatib and Dr. Mamduh 
al-'Akar, who participated in the Palestinian delegation to the 
Washington talks. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

