<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-NES-94-080 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  25 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Urayqat Heads Committee on Elections Preparations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Urayqat Heads Committee on Elections Preparations </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2504102894 Tel Aviv HA'ARETZ in Hebrew 25 Apr 94 p A4 </F>
<F P=103> TA2504102894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv HA'ARETZ </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Yosi Torpstein] </F>
  [Text] The Palestinians have started preparing for 
elections to the Palestinian self-government council. A 
committee on general and municipal elections has recently 
started operating at Orient House, the Palestinian headquarters 
in East Jerusalem. 
  The committee, headed by Dr. Sa'ib 'Urayqat, deputy head of 
the Palestinian delegation to the Washington negotiations, is 
working on the structure and powers of the council and on the 
manner in which the elections will be held. The committee 
members, some of whom are lawyers, represent the West Bank and 
the Gaza Strip. 
  The Palestinian Center for Statistics, set up several months 
ago in Jerusalem, has started drafting lists of Palestinian 
residents in the territories which will help in the preparation 
of voters lists. 
  The elections committee is about to send 30 Palestinian 
academics to Germany to study the issues of general and 
municipal elections. The studies, sponsored by the Germans, will 
include the management and conduct of elections, methods of 
defining constituencies, and so on. The course will start at 
the beginning of June and will last three weeks. At the end of 
the course, the academics will return and serve as instructors 
in local classes. 
  According to the Declaration of Principles [DOP] of 13 
September 1993, general elections for the Palestinian 
self-government council are to be held in the Gaza Strip and the 
West Bank nine months after the DOP goes into effect and after 
the negotiations on the council and the elections are completed. 
According to the DOP timetable, the elections were supposed to 
be held in July but, due to the delay in the completion of the 
negotiations on the Israeli withdrawal from Gaza and Jericho, 
the elections will probably be postponed. 
  Palestinian sources have reported that municipal elections 
may be held in the territories before the elections to the 
autonomy council take place. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-14016 </DOCNO>
