<H3> <TI>   Islamic Group's Military Wing Leader Killed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Islamic Group's Military Wing Leader Killed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2504141494 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1355 GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2504141494 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 25 Apr (MENA) -- Terrorist Tal'at Yasin 
Hammam, leader of the military wing of the so-called Islamic 
Group [IG], was killed in his hideout in Hada'iq al-Qubbah, 
Cairo, at dawn today during a shootout with the State Security 
detectives, who had to shoot back at him. 
  His death is considered as one of the successful strikes at 
local terrorist leaders and their failing attempts to shake 
Egyptian security and stability. 

</TEXT>

