<F P=101> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   PLO's 'Abbas Departs; 'Arafat To Meet Christopher </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PLO's 'Abbas Departs; 'Arafat To Meet Christopher </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2604114594 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1110 GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2604114594 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 26 Apr (MENA) -- PLO Executive Committee 
member Mahmud 'Abbas, alias Abu-Mazin, left Cairo for Tunis at 
noon today at the end of a two-day [as received] visit to Egypt. 
  Palestinian Ambassador in Cairo Zuhdi al-Qidrah, who saw 
Abu-Mazin off, said that during his visit to Cairo the 
Palestinian official was informed of the progress in the 
Palestinian-Israeli talks. He also met members of the 
Palestinian delegation to the negotiations and gave guidance 
regarding some issues on the negotiating table. 
  Al-Qidrah said Palestinian president Yasir 'Arafat would 
arrive in Cairo in the next few hours to meet President Muhammad 
Husni Mubarak and U.S. Secretary of State Warren Christopher 
during his visit to Egypt tomorrow. The talks will deal with 
developments in the peace process. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

