<H3> <TI>   League Denies Iraqi Minister Detained at Airport </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    League Denies Iraqi Minister Detained at Airport </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2504160394 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1530 GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2504160394 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 25 Apr (MENA)--An official source in the Arab 
League today denied a report by a weekly opposition paper that 
the State Security Detectives Service at Cairo International 
Airport detained Iraqi Justice Minister Shabib Lazim al-Maliki, 
who arrived in Cairo yesterday to attend the meetings of the 
Arab Justice Ministers Executive Bureau in the league 
secretariat. 
  The source said that the Iraqi minister was received at the 
airport by the Arab League assistant secretary general. 
  In a statement today, the source said that the assistant 
secretary general for legal affairs and Iraq's permanent 
delegate to the Arab League received the Iraqi minister in the 
VIP lounge and that they all left the airport without any 
problems shortly after the minister's arrival. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

