<H3> <TI>   Russian First Deputy Prime Minister Visits </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russian First Deputy Prime Minister Visits </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Makes Statement </H4>

<F P=102> JN2504141294 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 1115 GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2504141294 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Russian First Deputy Prime Minister Oleg Soskovets 
and the delegation accompanying him arrived in Damascus at noon 
today on a three-day official visit to Syria. He was received 
at Damascus International Airport by Dr. Salim Yasin, deputy 
prime minister for economic affairs; Dr. Muhammad al-'Imadi, 
minister of economy and foreign trade; several Foreign Ministry 
officials; Aleksandr Zotov, the Russian ambassador in Damascus; 
and the Embassy staff. 
  In a statement to the SYRIAN ARAB NEWS AGENCY, SANA, 
correspondent, Soskovets expressed his happiness over his visit 
to Syria, and said: My visit to Syria is linked to President 
Yeltsin's decision to continue and promote economic and 
political relations with Syria. He added: Our country has 
long-standing relations with Syria, and now that it has become 
an independent and sovereign state, we want to promote and 
expand previous relations and cooperation between the two 
countries. 

</TEXT>

