<F P=100> SYRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russian First Deputy Prime Minister Visits </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russian First Deputy Prime Minister Visits </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Official Talks Begin </H4>

<F P=102> JN2504183594 Damascus Syrian Arab Television Network in 
Arabic 1730 GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2504183594 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] The Syrian side led by Dr. Salim Yasin, deputy 
prime minister for economic affairs, and the Russian side led by 
Oleg Soskovets, first deputy prime minister of the Russian 
Federation, began official talks at the Prime Ministry this 
evening. [passage omitted] 
  At the beginning of the meeting, Dr. Yasin welcomed 
Soskovets 
and his accompanying delegation and wished them a happy stay in 
Syria. He also stressed the profound friendly relations that 
have long linked the two countries. He then referred to the 
strong ties, which have developed in all areas, as well as the 
positive results they have produced and will continue to 
produce. He also pointed to the fact that both sides recognize 
that they have joint interests and seek to activate, expand, and 
diversify these ties. He also stressed the need to exert every 
effort and embark on every cooperative effort to reap the fruits 
within this framework. 
  Soskovets then spoke, expressing his happiness over the warm 
reception accorded him and his delegation. He said: This visit 
has been planned for a long time, and we sought to make it 
successful and fruitful in the field of bilateral cooperation. 
He then referred to the political and economic developments in 
Russia over the past period, as well as the great changes it has 
seen. The two sides then reviewed several issues of common 
interest in various areas, as well as bilateral relations and 
ways of promoting them in the interest of both countries. 
  At the end of the session, both sides agreed to resume the 
meetings tomorrow morning at the level of bilateral and 
specialized committees. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

