<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Peres: Iran Responsible for Arad </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Peres: Iran Responsible for Arad </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2504064294 Tel Aviv IDF Radio in Hebrew 0500 GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA2504064294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv IDF Radio </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres said yesterday 
that Israel holds Iran responsible for the fate of captive 
navigator Ron Arad. As recalled, in reply to a question posed 
by an IDF radio correspondent, the Iranian foreign minister 
denied that any Israeli prisoners are being held on Iranian 
soil. Iran is now officially denying that its foreign minister 
ever spoke to a Zionist correspondent. Our correspondent Eyal 
Eisenstein spoke with Foreign Minister Peres: 
  [Begin recording] [Eisenstein] Foreign Minister Shim'on 
Peres was skeptical with regard to Iranian Foreign Minister 'Ali 
Akbar Velayati's statements on the issue of the Israeli POW's 
and MIA's. Yesterday, Peres said that Israel still considers 
Iran responsible for the fate of captive navigator Ron Arad. 
  [Peres] Iran's word carries no particular weight. Iran has 
no problem with making up or denying stories, without any 
foundation. Therefore, regardless of this or that statement, we 
shall continue to regard Iran as the main party responsible for 
the fate of Ron Arad. [passage omitted] [end recording] 

</TEXT>

