<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Informal Business Ties' With Tunisia To Be Formed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Informal Business Ties' With Tunisia To Be Formed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2404062994 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0500 GMT 24 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2404062994 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Economy and Planning Minister Shim'on Shetrit met 
yesterday in Bucharest with Tunisian Economic Minister Mohamed 
Ghannouchi [title as heard]. In their meeting, the two men 
agreed that informal business ties should be established between 
Israel and Tunisia as an introductory step toward the tightening 
of trade and tourism relations between the two countries. 
Shetrit and Ghannouchi agreed that some of these ties should be 
conducted through a third country. This was reported by our 
correspondent Gid'on Kouts. 

</TEXT>

