<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Four Iraqis Cross From Jordan Seeking Asylum </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Four Iraqis Cross From Jordan Seeking Asylum </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2304114694 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1100 GMT 23 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2304114694 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Four more Iraqi citizens last night entered Israel 
from across the Jordanian border, seeking political asylum in 
Israel. Our correspondent Karmela Menashe reports that they 
crossed the border fence near the Allenby Bridge, and were 
arrested by IDF [Israel Defense Forces] soldiers. They were 
unarmed. Two days ago, two Iraqi citizens crossed the border 
from Jordan near Kefar Rupin. 

</TEXT>

