<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Tzomet Central Committee Approves New Constitution </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Tzomet Central Committee Approves New Constitution </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2504105194 Tel Aviv HA'ARETZ in Hebrew 25 Apr 94 p A5 </F>
<F P=103> TA2504105194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv HA'ARETZ </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Yerah Tal] </F>
  [Excerpt] Last night, the Tzomet Central Committee 
approved the new party constitution by a majority of 58 to 30. 
Only 90 of the 250 committee members attended the vote. 
  Sources in Tzomet said that the fact that the constitution, 
which was supported by Tzomet Chairman Refa'el Eytan, did not 
win a sweeping majority is a further indication that Eytan is 
losing his power in Tzomet. 
  According to the new constitution, the chairman may appoint 
party functionaries, and his only obligation is to report the 
appointment to the party council and management. It was also 
decided that the chairman will be the party's candidate for 
prime minister and will be authorized to select and appoint 
candidates for the posts of minister and deputy minister, 
needing only to present the list to the Central Committee 
without asking for its authorization. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

