<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ship Carrying Feed Turned Back by U.S. Inspectors </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ship Carrying Feed Turned Back by U.S. Inspectors </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2604074594 Amman AL-RA'Y in Arabic 26 Apr 94 p 24 </F>
<F P=103> JN2604074594 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman AL-RA'Y </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] U.S. naval inspectors have turned back a ship 
bound for the Port of al-'Aqabah carrying a consignment of 3,943 
tonnes of soya feed for a Jordanian merchant. The vessel had 
been intercepted at the Strait of Tiran. 
  The inspection team explained that the lower quarters of the 
vessel had proved inaccessible to them. 
  The ship had to return for refueling at the Port of Suez. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

