<F P=100> India </F>
<H3> <TI>   Commission Recommends Action Against Border Troops </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Commission Recommends Action Against Border Troops </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2204151094 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1430 
GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2204151094 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The government has accepted all the recommendations 
of the National Human Rights Commission regarding the Bijbiara 
firing incident in Jammu and Kashmir, in which 31 persons were 
killed on the 22d of October last. The commission's 
recommendations included continuing of disciplinary proceedings 
and prosecution of 14 BSF [Border Security Force] personnel 
involved in the incident, payment of interim compensation to the 
victims, and a thorough review of deployment of BSF units in 
civilian areas. 
  In its compliance report, the government informed the 
commission that BSF authorities have been instructed to complete 
the record of evidence, proceedings against the personnel. In 
addition, the investigation by the local police has been 
completed and steps are being taken to file a charge-sheet in a 
civil court. Regarding compensation, the state government has 
disbursed ex-gratia relief of 100,000 rupees each to the next of 
kin of the 31 civilians who were killed in the incident. 

</TEXT>

