the Muslim world would have better knowledge of the atrocities 
being perpetrated by the Indian forces in the held valley. The 
spokesman hoped that the ambassadors will be allowed free access 
to visit all parts of the held valley, including the sites of 
recent massacres in Sopor and Bijbiara, and to meet the Kashmiri 
leaders, including those under detention. However, the 
spokesman said according to our information, unfortunately, it 
appears that once again this visit will be a conducted tour. 

</TEXT>

