<H3> <TI>   Fisheries Cooperation Agreement Signed With Ireland </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fisheries Cooperation Agreement Signed With Ireland </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2604162094 Tehran IRIB Television First Program Network in 
Persian 1430 GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2604162094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRIB Television First Program Network </F>
<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On the basis of a memorandum of understanding signed 
today between Construction Jihad Minister Gholam Reza Foruzesh 
and Irelands' Defense and Marine Minister David Andrews, the two 
countries decided to cooperate in fishing industries, including 
caviar, prawn, and canned fish trade and the export of the said 
products to Ireland and other countries. 
  Granting study bursaries to Iranian students studying 
fishing 
industries, marine wild life, and maritime installations, as 
well as the decision to hold training workshops in Iran and 
Ireland were among the key aspects of the agreement reached 
between the two ministers. 

</TEXT>

