<H3> <TI>   MKO Radio Reportedly Hails Assassination Attempt </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    MKO Radio Reportedly Hails Assassination Attempt </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2704122994 Tehran IRNA in English 1125 GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2704122994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, April 27, IRNA -- The terrorist Mujahideen 
Khalq Organization (MKO) has backed the aborted attempt on the 
life of the substitute Friday prayer leader of Mashhad Hojjat 
ol-Eslam Aba'i Khorasani, on April 22. In a radio broadcast 
from Iraq, the terrorist grouplet described the failed 
assassination attempt as a popular move without mentioning its 
links with the assassin. 
  An armed assailant, identified by the Ministry of 
Information 
as 'Ali Huri, shot and wounded Hojjat ol-Eslam Khorasani on 
Friday. He was later arrested by worshippers and handed over to 
police. Huri has confessed to his link with the Iraq-based 
terrorist grouplet and the MKO has not denied the link. 

</TEXT>

