<H3> <TI>   Further on Shahaq Remarks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further on Shahaq Remarks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2604130794 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1105 GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2604130794 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 26 Apr (MENA)--General Amnon Shahaq, Israeli 
deputy chief of staff and head of the Israeli delegation to the 
Gaza-Jericho negotiations, has said that the negotiators have 
completed 50 percent of an agreement. 
  In a news conference at noon today, Shahaq said the Israeli 
delegation would stay in Cairo until Thursday. If no agreement 
on all the points has been reached by then, he said, another 
round of negotiations will be held. 
  Shahaq said he has no information about a meeting in Cairo 
among Palestinian President Yasir 'Arafat, Israeli Foreign 
Minister Shim'on Peres, and U.S. Secretary of State Warren 
Christopher. 

</TEXT>

