<H3> <TI>   Al-Tibi: Agreement Depends on Prisoners' Release </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Tibi: Agreement Depends on Prisoners' Release </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2604192994 Jerusalem New Channel 2 Television Network in 
Hebrew 1700 GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2604192994 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem New Channel 2 Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Aharon Barne'a video report from Cairo] </F>
  [Excerpts] There will be no agreement between the PLO and 
Israel unless a timetable is determined for the release of all 
Palestinian prisoners, including Hamas [Islamic Resistance 
Movement] members. This was said today by Dr. Ahmad al-Tibi, 
'Arafat's adviser. It was reported in Cairo today that the 
delegations will continue their meetings next week. The date 
for the signing of the agreement has still not been determined. 
  [Begin recording] [passage omitted] [Al-Tibi] Without an 
agreed-upon timetable for the release of all the Palestinian 
prisoners there will be no agreement. 
  [Barne'a] Are you referring to all the prisoners, including 
Hamas people? 
  [Al-Tibi] All the prisoners are Palestinians, and the PLO is 
the legitimate leadership of the entire Palestinian people, 
therefore it is responsible for all prisoners, regardless of 
their affiliation. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

