<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Liaison Committee To Meet; Disputes Detailed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Liaison Committee To Meet; Disputes Detailed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2604181594 Algiers Voice of Palestine in Arabic 1702 GMT 
26 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2604181594 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Voice of Palestine </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Sources described as informed have said that the 
Palestinian-Israeli Liaison Committee, which is chaired by 
brother Abu-Mazin [Mahmud 'Abbas], member of the PLO Executive 
Committee, and Israeli Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres, will meet 
next Thursday [28 April] if the current dispute over a number of 
issues before the Palestinian-Israeli negotiations persists. 
Each side is insisting on its stance vis-a-vis a number of 
fundamental issues. 
  Palestinian sources have said that the Israeli side in the 
negotiations is insisting on its position regarding the topic of 
travel documents that the self-rule authority will provide to 
the Palestinian citizens. They are insisting on writing State 
of Israel on the cover while the Palestinian side stresses that 
this is unacceptable because it deprives the self rule of all 
authority. 
  The other fundamental point of contention is the subjugation 
of the coasts of Gaza to an Israeli authority, especially in the 
Khan Yunis area. 
  Regarding passage between Jericho and Gaza, the Israeli 
position has retracted in the new round of negotiations, 
expressing reservations over the passage linking the two areas. 
The Israeli side is proposing to make the link by air in order 
to avoid accidents in the future. The Israeli side also refuses 
to grant the right of the self-ruling authority to issue postage 
stamps under the pretext that what is being negotiated is a 
transitional self rule, while the travel document and the stamps 
represent manifestations of a state. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

