<H3> <TI>   Committee Ends Session in Algiers </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Committee Ends Session in Algiers </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2604225294 Algiers Radio Algiers Network in Arabic 2200 
GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2604225294 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Radio Algiers Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] The proceedings of the 28th ordinary session of 
the Arab Maghreb Union [AMU] follow-up committee ended at 
El-Djazair Hotel in Algiers this evening. This is the first 
session to be held since Algeria took over the chairmanship of 
the union for the current year. The participants discussed a 
number of issues relating to the progress achieved in the 
building of the Maghreb edifice. 
  The heads of the delegations representing the five Maghreban 
states also discussed the union's relations with the other 
regional blocs and with regional and international financial 
institutions. 
  In his closing speech, Ahmed Attaf, the chairman of the 
session and secretary of state in charge of cooperation and 
Maghreban affairs in Algeria -- given that Algeria has been 
chairing the AMU since March -- expressed his satisfaction with 
the results achieved by the session which, he said, would 
undoubtedly contribute to strengthening the Maghreban process 
and increase its dynamism and activity. He added that the 
committee would follow-up the realization of the programs drawn 
up by the session, particularly the sectors that require serious 
attention. 
  AMU Secretary-General Mohamed Amamou, for his part, read out 
a thank-you message addressed to President Liamine Zeroual in 
which he wished him total success in carrying out his mission as 
current president of the Arab Maghreb Union. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

