<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Arafat, Egyptian Envoy Discuss Talks, Cairo Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Arafat, Egyptian Envoy Discuss Talks, Cairo Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2704061194 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in 
Arabic 0500 GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2704061194 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Palestinian President Yasir 'Arafat last night 
received Ibrahim 'Allam, Egypt's Ambassador to Tunisia. 
Following the session, Ambassador 'Allam said that he and 
President 'Arafat reviewed the Palestinian-Israeli talks 
currently under way in Cairo and Paris, the current efforts 
designed to overcome the obstacles at these talks, as well as 
preparations for 'Arafat's visit to Cairo due to take place 
today, Wednesday. 
  Meanwhile, the Palestinian news agency WAFA reports that the 
Egyptian ambassador conveyed an important message to 'Arafat 
from the Egyptian leadership dealing with recent political 
developments in the region. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

