<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-Husayni Comments on Security in Gaza, Jericho </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Husayni Comments on Security in Gaza, Jericho </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2704114394 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1015 GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2704114394 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 27 Apr (MENA)--Dr. Faysal al-Husayni, head of 
the advisory committee of the Palestinian delegation at the 
Washington peace talks, has emphasized that Israel's failure to 
grant the Palestinians full authority in Gaza and Jericho will 
result in ineffective control over the security situation. 
  In a statement today, he said: We must have a complete 
authority so that security will be achieved for everyone. 
  He expressed his hope that Palestinian President Yasir 
'Arafat's meeting with U.S. Secretary of State Warren 
Christopher will result in resolving the problems blocking the 
peace process. He also hoped that the U.S. side, as a cosponsor 
of the peace conference, will persuade the Israelis to change 
some of their policies on the negotiations. 
  Al-Husayni affirmed that his visit to Egypt is private and 
has nothing to do with the negotiations or with Palestinian 
President Yasir 'Arafat's visit to Cairo. 
  He announced that a meeting is expected to be held between 
representatives of the Palestinians inside the occupied 
territories and the PLO leadership in Tunis next week as part of 
continuous coordination in preparation for the next stage once 
an agreement to implement the Gaza-Jericho Accord is signed. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

