<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Executive Memeber Urges `Escalation' of Confrontation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Executive Memeber Urges `Escalation' of Confrontation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2604131694 London AL-HAYAH in Arabic 24 Apr 94 p3 </F>
<F P=103> PM2604131694 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-HAYAH </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Al-Surani Urges Escalation of </F>
Confrontation With Israelis"] 
  [Text] Cairo, AL-HAYAH -- PLO Executive Committee Member 
Jamal al-Surani has reaffirmed "the need for the continuation of 
the intifadah in the occupied Palestinian territory and for the 
escalation of confrontational operations against the Israelis to 
force them to speed up their withdrawal." 
  Although the signing of the Gaza-Jericho agreement is 
imminent, al-Surani, who is opposed to the Declaration of 
Principles agreement, believes that "the Palestinian-Israeli 
negotiation sessions have exposed Israel's lies about its desire 
for peace and also exposed its continuing refusal to implement 
the UN resolutions and its violation of the fourth Geneva 
Convention." 
  In a statement to AL-HAYAH, al-Surani described the 
agreement 
between Fatah and the Islamic Resistance Movement (Hamas) as "a 
step toward unification of the various Palestinian factions 
within the framework of the PLO, the sole legitimate 
representative of the Palestinian people." 
  He accused the U.S. Administration of "appeasing" Israel. He 
added that when the Palestinians "defend their rights they are 
accused of terrorism but the Israeli repression and murders are 
seen by them as security preccautions." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

