<H3> <TI>   Signatories to Anti-'Arafat Memorandum Named </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Signatories to Anti-'Arafat Memorandum Named </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2604162294 Jerusalem AL-QUDS in Arabic 26 Apr 94 pp 1, 19 </F>
<F P=103> TA2604162294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem AL-QUDS </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By Zaki Abu-al-Halawah and Muhammad Abu-Khudayr] </F>
  [Excerpts] Jerusalem -- In a memorandum addressed to 
Palestinian and international public opinion, leading 
Palestinian figures in the occupied territories warned that any 
Israeli-Palestinian agreement that fails to respond to the 
Palestinian people's legitimate and natural rights will not 
achieve a just and comprehensive peace in the region. [passage 
omitted] 
  The memorandum was signed by Haydar 'Abd-al-Shafi, Mamduh 
al- 
'Akir, Su'ad al-'Amiri, Jabi Baramaki, Yunus al-Jaru, Ahmad 
Hamzah al-Natshah, 'Abd-al-Hadi Abu-Khusa, Muhammad Zayn-al-Din, 
'Abd-al-Jawad Salih, Mustafa al-Barghuthi, Ghassan al-Khatib, 
'Abd-al-Hafiz al-Ashhab, Samir 'Abdallah, Shawkat Zayd 
al-Kilani, Iyad al-Sarraj, Sharif al-Musa, Raja Shihadah, Hani 
'Arafat, Raji al-Surani, Fayyad al-Fayyad, Muhammad Zaki 
al-Radwan, Farid Abu-Wardah, and Sami Abu-Sha'ban. 

</TEXT>

