<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hamas Threatens Attacks If Prisoners Not Released </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hamas Threatens Attacks If Prisoners Not Released </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2704064194 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 0400 GMT 27 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2704064194 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Hamas terrorists are threatening to carry out a 
wave of attacks and kidnappings if all Hamas [Islamic Resistance 
Movement] prisoners are not released from jail. The threat came 
in a leaflet claiming responsibility for last week's murder of 
Israeli soldier Shahar Simhoni. The leaflet carries a photocopy 
of Simhoni's ID card. Meanwhile, arrests are continuing in the 
Janin area, of Hamas members connected to the Hadera bombing. 
More on these developments from reporter Alan Ben-'Ami: 
  [Ben-'Ami] The Hamas leaflet distributed in the Gaza Strip 
says that members of 'Izz-al-Dan al-Qassam's Squad No. 6 
kidnapped and killed soldier Shahar Simhoni last week. 
According to the leaflet, which reproduced the soldier's ID 
card and driver's license, the terrorists passed themselves off 
as Jews, grabbed Simhoni, who was on his way to his girlfriend 
from his Army base, and after a short struggle, killed him. 
[passage omitted] 
  The leaflet is addressed to Prime Minister Rabin and demands 
that he immediately release all Hamas prisoners, especially the 
Hamas leader Shaykh Ahmad Yasin and Hamas members captured in 
recent weeks. If not, the leaflet warns, the killing or 
kidnapping of Israelis will continue. The threats are coming 
against the backdrop of a major crack down on Hamas by security 
forces. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

