<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] India has described Islamabad's decision to hold 
elections in the northern areas of Pakistan-occupied Kashmir as 
a cosmetic exercise intended to perpetuate illegal occupation. 
In response to a query by newsmen in New Delhi, the External 
Affairs Ministry spokesman said Islamabad has denied democratic 
rights and violated the human rights of the people of the 
region, which was occupied by it through aggression four decades 
ago. The spokesman said the recurring violence including 
sectarian strifes speak of the political alienation, economic 
deprivation, and backwardness of the people in the region. 

