<F P=105>  Urdu </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In occupied Kashmir, seven Indian troops were killed 
and several seriously injured in a bloody clash with freedom 
fighters near Bijbiara on the Srinagar-Jammu Highway. A large 
contingent of Indian troops and paramilitary forces immediately 
left for Bijbiara to deal with any situation. A report says a 
youth was tortured to death in Pampur near Srinagar. Another 
youth under military custody was also martyred. 
  Meanwhile, in retaliatory action, freedom fighters attacked 
a 
number of paramilitary troops and injured them. According to 
Kashmir Media Service, 32 innocent youths were arrested today 
and taken to interrogation centers, where torture by the Indian 
Army is common. 

