<H3> <TI>   Government Approves German, U.S. Joint Ventures </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Approves German, U.S. Joint Ventures </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2804050594 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0245 
GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2804050594 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The government has approved setting up of a joint 
venture company with Germany in the field of engineering. It 
will have collaboration between the Mettalurgical and 
Engineering Consultants India Limited, MECON, and LPOAG 
[expansion unknown] of Germany. The new company will have an 
initial paid-up capital of 40 lakh rupees with the German 
company contributing 74 percent. The company will deal with 
designing and manufacturing of electrical, electronic 
automation, and electro mechanical equipment for industrial 
plants. 
  The union cabinet also approved another joint venture 
company 
by MECON with a U.S. computer software company. It will harness 
information technology for mettalurgical, chemical, and refining 
industries. It will have equity of two and a half crore rupees. 

</TEXT>

