<F P=100> Sudan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Statement Issued on Abduction of Ambassador to Somalia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Statement Issued on Abduction of Ambassador to Somalia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA2704195094 Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network in 
Arabic 1500 GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA2704195094 </F>
<F P=104>  Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Sudanese ambassador to Somalia, 'Abd-al-Baqi 
Muhammad Hasan Ahmad, was released in Mogadishu today after 
continuous negotiations with his abductors, Foreign Ministry 
officials, and relevant organs. Four armed people abducted the 
ambassador on 19 April. This act was strongly condemned in all 
quarters, especially by the leaders of the tribe to which the 
abductors belong, and who exerted an appreciable effort obtain 
the ambassador's release. 
  The Foreign Ministry, in a statement issued today, commended 
all those who contributed to the release of Ambassador 
'Abd-al-Baqi, particularly all concerned Somali organizations 
and groups. The statement also praised the role played by the 
Sudanese ambassador in Mogadishu, under very complicated 
circumstances. The Foreign Ministry confirmed that this 
unexpected crisis would not affect the firm relations that bind 
the Sudanese and Somali peoples. The statement confirmed that 
the Government of Sudan would continue to offer all it could to 
contribute to achieving security, stability and development in 
Somalia. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

