<F P=100> Sudan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister Discusses Peace Talks With Kenyan Envoy </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister Discusses Peace Talks With Kenyan Envoy </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA2704174794 Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network in 
Arabic 1300 GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA2704174794 </F>
<F P=104>  Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Husayn Sulayman Abu-Salih today 
held discussions in his office at the ministry with the Kenyan 
ambassador on preparations for the coming round of peace 
negotiations, to be held in Nairobi, Kenya, on 16 May. Dr. 
Abu-Salih assured the Kenyan ambassador of Sudan's eagerness to 
establish peace in the south within the framework of a unified 
Sudan, without becoming a pawn of foreign forces. He expressed 
his hope that the forthcoming Nairobi round would be decisive, 
and that the rebel movement would come with clear views to 
assist in solving the problem. 
  The meeting touched on Kenyan-Sudanese relations. The two 
sides confirmed their eagerness to strengthen and develop those 
relations. 
  Dr. Husayn Sulayman Abu-Salih also met today with Mr. Peter 
Hansen, UN assistant secretary general for humanitarian affairs, 
who is currently visiting the country. Dr. Abu-Waf, minister of 
state at the ministry of social planning, and Mr. Ali Muhammad 
Yasin, Sudan's delegate to the United Nations, were also 
present. The meeting dealt with issues connected with 
humanitarian conditions. Dr. Abu-Salih affirmed Sudan's 
cooperation with all those working in the humanitarian field to 
deliver food to the citizens in all areas affected by the war, 
via Operation Lifeline. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

