<F P=100> ARAB AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Algeria </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister Views Maghreb Economic Ties </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Minister Views Maghreb Economic Ties </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2704164094 Algiers Radio Algiers Network in Arabic 1200 
GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2704164094 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Radio Algiers Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] Our colleague Saliha Bahri 
asked Foreign Minister Mohamed Salah Dembri yesterday what he 
thought about chances for transforming the Arab Maghreb Union 
into a regional bloc and about its relations with the European 
Union. 
  [Begin Dembri recording] In theory this is an easy option 
for 
us. However, when it comes to practice it is necessary to first 
build the Maghreb bloc up as a strong economic group, a matter 
which has yet to be achieved. The European Community has had 30 
years of experience behind it before it was possible to realize 
a strong economy and abolish borders between European countries. 
As far as we are concerned we are still at the beginning; it is 
necessary for us now to examine all aspects of trade: individual 
movement and everything else. We have to build the Maghreb 
house first before one can talk as a bloc with any other bloc in 
the world. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

