<F P=100> ARAB AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Algeria </F>
<H3> <TI>   Economic Workshop Attended by Government Officials </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Economic Workshop Attended by Government Officials </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Workshop Makes Recommendations </H4>

<F P=102> LD2804085794 Algiers Radio Algiers Network in Arabic 0600 
GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2804085794 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Radio Algiers Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] The information and study workshop on the 
prospects for the Algerian economy, which was set up by the 
presidency and government and in which members of the government 
and the main social and economic operators participated, has 
issued its recommendations. In the recommendations, the 
participants urge that a start be made this year on drawing up a 
comprehensive and coherent program for institutional reforms and 
restructuring, in order to free the initiative of economic 
operators and reintroduce a market economy mechanism. 
  The participants also recommended that as soon as possible 
work should begin on drawing up a coherent program to 
restructure the public sector in order to increase output; work 
should also begin on the reorganization and diversification of 
the activities of banks. They also recommended the 
reintroduction of a system that would encourage partnership. 
  Concerning the social sphere, the participants stressed the 
importance of bolstering the program for social and economic 
development, as part of the embodiment of social justice, 
through the consolidation of the national system of social 
security and the protection of the purchasing power of those 
strata who are below the poverty line. They also stressed the 
importance of bolstering dialogue and national solidarity. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

