<F P=101> Algeria </F>
<H3> <TI>   Student Killed, Doctor Wounded in `Terrorist' Attacks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Student Killed, Doctor Wounded in `Terrorist' Attacks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2804035094 Algiers Radio Algiers Network in Arabic 2200 
GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2804035094 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Radio Algiers Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A statement by the security services today announced 
that Moulay Tahar, a 45-year-old doctor working in the capital, 
was the victim of a terrorist attack on 26 April at about 1115 
hours. The source said that Moulay was wounded after two armed 
people stormed his office located in a clinic at Makaria in the 
municipality of Hussein Dey. 
  A 16-year-old student at Sadadou Mourad secondary school was 
also the subject of a terrorist attack yesterday at Meftah, in 
the province of Blida, south of the capital. The security 
services' statement said that the victim, who was attacked by a 
group of terrorists armed with automatic pistols and sawn-off 
shot guns, died of his wounds on the spot. 

</TEXT>

