<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Barzani Party Denies Conditions for Damascus Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Barzani Party Denies Conditions for Damascus Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2604190794 (Clandestine) Voice of Iraqi Kurdistan in 
Arabic 1530 GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2604190794 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of Iraqi Kurdistan </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Letter from the Kurdistan Democratic Party's Central Public </F>
Relations Office to the London-based Arabic daily AL-HAYAH; date 
not given] 
  [Text] To the esteemed AL-HAYAH newspaper: 
  Subject: Explanation 
  Greetings: 
  In its issue No. 11,386 dated 20 April 1994, your newspaper 
published an article by Kamiran Qurrah Daghi under the headline 
"Barzani Sets Three Conditions for Acceptance of Damascus 
Invitation." In order to shed light and explain the truth about 
what was published in the article, we ask that the following 
explanation be published: 
  1. Our party's relations with Syria are strong. They are 
based on mutual respect and understanding. We attach great 
importance to these relations. 
  2. His Excellency President Hafiz al-Asad has kindly 
received Mr. Barzani during all his visits to Syria. Mr. 
Barzani has strong and close relations with President Hafiz 
al-Asad. 
  3. We would like to explain that Barzani would not set 
conditions for visiting Syria. He regards Syria as his own 
country. The doors of Damascus have always been and still are 
open and there is no need for friends to set conditions among 
themselves. 
  Please accept our regards. 
  Signed: The Central Public Relations Office 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

