<DOCNO> FBIS4-14164 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drnes082_c_94005" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-NES-94-082 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  28 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reportage on Christopher, 'Arafat, Peres Visits </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reportage on Christopher, 'Arafat, Peres Visits </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Christopher, Musa, 'Arafat Confer </H4>

<F P=102> NC2804094394 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0930 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2804094394 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 28 Apr (MENA)--Foreign Minister 'Amr Musa met 
U.S. Secretary of State Warren Christopher at the Foreign 
Ministry this morning. Christopher arrived in Cairo from Saudi 
Arabia last night as part of his tour of the region. 
  Palestinian President Yasir 'Arafat arrived at the Foreign 
Ministry leading a delegation and joined the meeting between 
Musa and Christopher. They will discuss ways to remove the 
latest obstacles blocking the signing of the Gaza-Jericho Accord 
between the Palestinians and Israelis. 
  The delegation accompanying 'Arafat includes the head of the 
Palestinian side at the Gaza-Jericho talks, Dr. Nabil Sha'th, 
PLO Executive Committee member Yasir 'Abd-Rabbuh, and Marwan 
Kanafani. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

