<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 27 Apr (MENA)--President Husni Mubarak has 
asked the Yemeni leaders to exercise self-restraint and to avoid 
intensifying the problems in Yemen. He warned of the gravity of 
any escalation in the situation and any acts of violence. 
  Mubarak made this statement during two telephone calls he 
received this afternoon from Yemeni Vice President 'Ali Salim 
al-Bid and from Yemeni President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih. He told 
Salih and al-Bid that confrontation between Yemeni brothers and 
forces will be detrimental to Yemeni interests and will threaten 
the country's security, stability, and unity of its sons. He 
called for settling their differences through dialogue and 
reason. 

