<H3> <TI>   'Abd-al-Rahman, Others Sentenced to Hard Labor </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Abd-al-Rahman, Others Sentenced to Hard Labor </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2804115894 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1110 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2804115894 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 28 Apr (MENA)--The Higher State Security 
Court-Emergency issued a ruling today in the case of the 
al-Fayyum rioting. It sentenced the following five defendants 
to seven years of hard labor: 'Umar Ahmad 'Abd-al-Rahman, 'Ali 
al-Sayyid 'Abd-al-Jayyid, Naji Sayyid 'Abdallah, Nabil 'Ali 
Jum'ah, and Khalid 'Abd-al-Majid Muhammad. 
  The court also sentenced 16 defendants to five years of hard 
labor and five other defendants to three years of hard labor. 
It acquitted 21 defendants and dropped criminal cases against 
two defendants because they had died. 

</TEXT>

