BFN 

  [Excerpt] Jordan has paid its last respects to the late 
Queen Zayn al-Sharaf, the queen mother, who passed away 
yesterday morning in Switzerland after a life fully dedicated to 
goodness and bounty. 
  King Husayn, who was in Britain for an ear operation, 
accompanied the body of the queen mother's final homecoming late 
last night. 
  The late queen's flag-draped coffin was carried on a gun 
carriage accompanied by an escort from Raghadan Palace to the 
Royal Guard's Mosque where the funeral prayers took place after 
which the body was laid to rest at the royal cemetery. 
  His Majesty the King, their royal highnesses the princes, 
and 
the sharifs, accepted condolences after the funeral. Thousands 
of mourners also paid their last respects to the late Queen Zayn. 
  The funeral was attended by foreign dignitaries, including 
the visiting president of Mali, and delegations from the PLO and 
Oman. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

