<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chinese Parliamentary Delegation Meets With Officials </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chinese Parliamentary Delegation Meets With Officials </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Received by Prime Minister </H4>

<F P=102> JN2404194794 Amman Jordan Television Network in Arabic 1700 
GMT 24 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2404194794 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Jordan Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Today, Prime Minister Dr. 'Abd-al-Salam al-Majali 
received at the Prime Ministry Wang Zhaoguo, vice chairman of 
the National Committee of the Chinese People's Political 
Consultative Conference [CPPCC], and his accompanying 
delegation. Senate Speaker Ahmad al-Lawzi attended the meeting. 
  Dr. al-Majali reviewed the development in Jordanian-Chinese 
relations, which both sides are seeking to develop in all 
fields. He stressed Jordan's continuous commitment to achieving 
a just, lasting, and comprehensive peace which restores the 
legitimate rights of the Palestinian people. He said that 
Jordan appreciates China's stands on various Arab issues. 
  For his part, the CPPCC vice chairman stressed the 
importance 
of reinforcing Jordanian-Chinese relations. He also expressed 
his support for Jordan's commitment to peace. 

</TEXT>

