<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister, Iranian Envoy Discuss Hostages </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Minister, Iranian Envoy Discuss Hostages </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2604201594 Tehran IRNA in English 1933 GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2604201594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, April 26, IRNA -- Iranian Ambassador to 
Lebanon, Homayun 'Alizadeh, met Lebanese Foreign Minister Faris 
Buwayz in Beirut last night to formally discuss the case of the 
four Iranian hostages kidnapped by the Christian Phalangists in 
1982. 
  The four, Charge D'affaires Mohsen Musavi, diplomat Ahmad 
Motevasellian, embassy worker Taqi Rastgar Moqaddam and 
photographer of the Islamic Republic News Agency (IRNA) Kazem 
Akhawan, who were kidnapped on the Beirut-Tripoli road are the 
longest held hostages. 
  Sources related to the Zionist regime insisted that the 
Iranian nationals were killed at Phalangist Militia Chief Samir 
Ja'ja's headquarters. 
  Ja'ja' said he was not responsible for kidnapping of the 
Iranian diplomats. 
  Despite Iran's repeated requests the case of the four 
Iranian 
has remained unresolved. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

