<AU>   FBIS-NES-94-082 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  27 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Peres: Palestinian Autonomy Practically `Independence' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Peres: Palestinian Autonomy Practically `Independence' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2704165994 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 1500 GMT 27 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2704165994 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] Foreign Minister Peres told 
the Knesset plenum that when the Palestinians are granted 
autonomy, it will practically be independence. 
  Referring to the Camp David accords, Peres said when the 
Likud Prime Minister Menahem Begin offered autonomy to all the 
Palestinian residents of Judaea and Samaria, the Likud should 
have known that autonomy is 80 percent, if not 90 percent, 
independence. Autonomy is not a reduction in their authority 
but basically sovereignty minus responsibility for two things: 
security and foreign relations. Peres later said we will let 
the Palestinians run their lives with honor and independence, 
again with the two exceptions. 
  The foreign minister was responding to a motion for the 
agenda by Likud Knesset Member Moshe Qatzav, who accused Peres 
of rushing the negotiations with the PLO at the expense of 
Israeli interests. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

