<H3> <TI>   Baraq Says PLO, Hamas Possess Similar Aims </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Baraq Says PLO, Hamas Possess Similar Aims </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2604164694 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1200 GMT 26 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2604164694 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Chief of Staff Ehud Baraq says the PLO and Hamas 
[Islamic Resistance Movement] represent two aspects of a 
national movement possessing rather similar long-term aims 
vis-a-vis Israel. Lieutenant General Baraq added, however, that 
the two organizations have different methods for arriving at 
these goals. 
  Our correspondent Yo'el Nir reports Lt. Gen. Baraq today 
briefed the Knesset Foreign Affairs and Defense Committee about 
reports on agreements between the PLO and Hamas. Baraq said 
that he will not be surprised if Hamas people join social 
networks in Gaza and Jericho, such as schools and welfare 
services. The chief of staff also said he will not be surprised 
if one faction of Hamas will pursue the path of terrorism. The 
chief of staff believes that the PLO will on the whole be 
interested in proving that terrorism is on the wane in the areas 
under their jurisdiction. 

</TEXT>

