<H3> <TI>   General: Syria Buying Scud Missiles in North Korea </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    General: Syria Buying Scud Missiles in North Korea </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2704114694 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1100 GMT 27 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2704114694 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Major General Ze'ev Livne, commander of the Home 
Front Command, said that Syria is continuing to procure 
launchers and Scud missiles from North Korea. He said that for 
the Home Front Command it does not matter where the missiles are 
launched, whether from Iran, Syria, or Iraq. However, if they 
are launched in Iran it poses much more complex operational 
problems. 
  The commander made the remarks to our Army affairs 
correspondent Karmela Menashe. The IDF [Israel Defense Forces] 
today fired a 155 mm gun into a concrete wall as part of a 
series of tests aimed at developing defenses for settlements 
along the confrontation lines to enable them to withstand a 
direct hit by a shell. 

</TEXT>

