<H3> <TI>   Settler Receives Life for Murdering `Terrorist' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Settler Receives Life for Murdering `Terrorist' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2804075194 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0700 GMT 28 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2804075194 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Jerusalem District Court sentenced Yoram 
Skolnik, from the settlement of Ma'ale Hever in the Hebron 
Hills, to life in prison. He was convicted of the premeditated 
murder of the terrorist Musa Sabah, whose hands and feet were 
bound after he was apprehended for having stabbed a settler near 
the settlement of Susya in the Hebron Hills. 

</TEXT>

