<F P=101> United Arab Emirates </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Receives Calls From Yemen's Salih, al-Bid </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President Receives Calls From Yemen's Salih, al-Bid </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2804080094 Manama WAKH in Arabic 0540 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN2804080094 </F>
<F P=104>  Manama WAKH </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Abu Dhabi, 27 Apr (WAKH)--His Highness Shaykh Zayid 
Bin-Sultan Al Nuhayyan, president of the United Arab Emirates, 
has received two telephone calls, one from Yemeni President 'Ali 
'Abdallah Salih, and another from Yemeni Vice President 'Ali 
Salim al-Bid. The conversations dealt with the acts of 
violence which took place between Yemeni forces in northern 
Sanaa today. 
  His Highness Shaykh Zayid called on the Yemeni president and 
vice president to exert every possible effort to contain the 
armed confrontation between the sons of the one people, to 
exercise self-restraint and patience, and to prevent the use of 
violence to solve the Yemeni crisis. He also called for 
adopting the principle of dialogue and reconciliation as the 
only means to end the Yemeni crisis and to stabilize the 
situation there. 

</TEXT>

