<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> United Arab Emirates </F>
<H3> <TI>   1st Armored Division Reportedly Launches Offensive </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    1st Armored Division Reportedly Launches Offensive </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Salih's Stepbrother Said To Lead Attack </H4>

<F P=102> NC2704154894 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1533 GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2704154894 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Aden, 27 Apr (MENA)--A responsible source at the 
Yemeni Socialist Party [YSP] Information Center has stated that 
at 1100 today the 1st Armored Division led by Colonel 'Ali 
Muhsin al-Ahmar, stepbrother of Yemeni President 'Ali 'Abdallah 
Salih, backed by other brigades brought in from Sanaa, launched 
an offensive. 
  The Yemeni source said that these forces launched a 
large-scale offensive with various types of weapons against the 
2nd Armored Brigade, deployed in 'Imran, which receives its 
orders from the defense minister. The source added that pitched 
battles involving the use of heavy weapons are still raging this 
afternoon. 
  The source said that the aggression against the southern 
brigade took place directly after President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih 
delivered a speech in al-Sab'ayn Square in Sanaa today to mark 
the 27 April occasion. In his speech, he called for removing 
the YSP from power. The source noted that the military 
escalation of the situation on this large a scale throughout 
Yemen will block the success of the mediation efforts being made 
to resolve the crisis peacefully. The YSP holds President Salih 
personally, and members of his family who occupy important posts 
in the military establishment, as the source put it, responsible 
for the grave consequences that may result from this offensive. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

