<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> United Arab Emirates </F>
<H3> <TI>   1st Armored Division Reportedly Launches Offensive </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    1st Armored Division Reportedly Launches Offensive </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    U.S., French Attaches Fired On in Camp </H4>

<F P=102> NC2704192794 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1852 GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2704192794 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sanaa, 27 Apr (MENA)--A Yemeni military source in 
Sanaa today accused the Yemeni Socialist Party [YSP] of causing 
the military situation in Yemen. In a statement this evening, 
the source said that at 1330 today while the military committee, 
accompanied by the U.S. and French military attaches, was 
visiting the 1st Armored Brigade and the 3d Armored Brigade in 
the 'Imran Camp in Sanaa Governorate, armed groups led by YSP 
member Yahya Dahish 'Alyan, an "old officer expelled from the 
Armed Forces," stormed the camp and began firing various small-, 
medium-, and large-caliber weapons as well as tank, artillery, 
and rocket fire. The source pointed out that the bombardment 
targeted the headquarters of the 1st Armored Brigade, the 
soldiers barracks, the central security camp nearby, and 
residential areas in the city of 'Imran. 
  The source said that the intensive bombardment caused heavy 
losses in lives and property. Dozens of people were martyred 
and others were injured, but the casualty toll has not been 
determined. The Yemeni military source expressed his regret for 
this incident. He said that President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih 
followed up on the situation from the very beginning and 
immediately issued instructions to the defense minister and the 
general chief of staff to quickly contain the situation and 
prevent any military deterioration. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

