<H3> <TI>   1st Armored Division Reportedly Launches Offensive </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    1st Armored Division Reportedly Launches Offensive </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Army Units Reportedly Resume Battles </H4>

<F P=102> JN2804104694 Paris Radio Monte Carlo in Arabic 1000 GMT 28 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2804104694 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris Radio Monte Carlo </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] It has been learned from a political source in Sanaa 
that battles between army units in the 'Imran area, north of the 
Yemeni capital resumed, this morning. The battles, in which 
armored vehicles and guns were used, resumed after the failure 
of a cease-fire between these opposing units, some of which are 
loyal to north Yemeni President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih and others 
to his southern rival Vice President 'Ali Salim al-Bid. 
  Yesterday's battles, which erupted in the same area, resumed 
strongly at dawn today. According to north and south Yemeni 
sources, the battles are still raging. No figures on casualties 
have been announced. Yesterday, sources said scores of people 
from both sides were killed or wounded, in addition to civilian 
casualties. 

</TEXT>

