<DOCNO> FBIS4-14232 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drnes082_j_94010" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-NES-94-082 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  28 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> United Arab Emirates </F>
<H3> <TI>   1st Armored Division Reportedly Launches Offensive </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    1st Armored Division Reportedly Launches Offensive </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Number of Killed, Wounded Reported </H4>

<F P=102> NC2804154594 Paris AFP in English 1528 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2804154594 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sanaa, April 28 (AFP) -- Fighting between Yemeni 
Army factions has killed more than 100 people and wounded 200 in 
the past two days, a team of Yemeni journalists who visited the 
scene said Thursday [28 April]. 
  The dead included 18 civilians. More than 85 tanks had been 
destroyed in the fighting between northern and southern armoured 
units north of Sanaa, according to the team, who included 
journalists from the independent Yemen Times. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

