<F P=101> United Arab Emirates </F>
<H3> <TI>   Salih Confers with U.S., French Envoys on Incident </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Salih Confers with U.S., French Envoys on Incident </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2804145994 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1400 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2804145994 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brother Lieutenant General 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, 
Presidential Council chairman, has received Arthur Hughes, the 
U.S. ambassador to our country. They discussed various issues 
of interest to bilateral relations. They also discussed 
developments in the situation in our country in light of the 
regrettable events at the 'Imran camp. 
  The brother chairman expressed profound regret and sorrow 
for 
the chaste Yemeni blood spilled as result of the reckless 
practices of some irresponsible elements. He said these 
practices aim to implement hostile designs to push the situation 
toward a military explosion, to circumvent the pledge and accord 
document, and to drive the people and their Armed Forces into 
the furnace of bloody fighting in order to destroy unity. He 
stressed there is no alternative to unity, democracy, security, 
and stability, no matter what the price. He expressed 
appreciation for the U.S. friends' interest in our country's 
security and stability and for their support for unity and 
democracy. 
  The brother chairman of the Presidential Council also 
received French Ambassador (Marcel Levin). They reviewed 
bilateral relations and the efforts being exerted to contain the 
crisis in light of the regrettable military developments and 
incidents in 'Imran yesterday. 
  The brother chairman stressed his eagerness to contain the 
situation and thwart all designs to stir up sedition and 
infighting among the children of the same homeland. He said 
dialogue and resorting to reason and wisdom are the only way to 
tackle all issues and problems. He expressed appreciation for 
France's efforts to support our country and its unity and 
democratization. 

</TEXT>

