<H3> <TI>   Salih, al-Bid Receive Messages From Mubarak </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Salih, al-Bid Receive Messages From Mubarak </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2704212494 Cairo MENA in Arabic 2050 GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2704212494 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sanaa, 27 Apr (MENA)--Yemeni President 'Ali 
'Abdallah Salih has received a message from Egyptian President 
Muhammad Husni Mubarak urging the Yemeni parties to stop the 
clashes and avoid a military confrontation to prevent shedding 
Yemeni blood. 
  The message was delivered by Egyptian Ambassador in Sanaa 
'Ata Mahmud Harun when the Yemeni president received him this 
evening. 
  President Mubarak called for dialogue among the parties to 
the conflict and for a halt to violence to preserve Yemeni unity. 
  The Egyptian ambassador also telephoned Yemeni Vice 
President 
'Ali Salim al-Bid this evening to convey a similar message from 
President Mubarak. 
  [Cairo MENA in Arabic at 2052 GMT on 27 April, in another 
Sanaa-datelined item, reports that the Yemeni foreign minister 
received a similar message from Egyptian Foreign Minister 'Amr 
Musa delivered by the Egyptian ambassador in Sanaa.] 

</TEXT>

