<F P=102>   JN2804172894 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1700 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2804172894 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brother Lieutenant General 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, 
Presidential Council chairman, this afternoon called on brother 
Dr. Hasan Muhammad Makki, the first deputy prime minister, who 
has been hospitalized following a sinful assassination bid 
today. The brother chairman inquired about brother Makki's 
health and expressed regret for this deplorable incident. He 
wished the brother first deputy prime minister speedy recovery. 
He also expressed condolences for the families of the three 
martyred escorts of the first deputy prime minister who fell in 
that regrettable incident. 
  The brother chairman was accompanied by brother Dr. Muhammad 
Sa'id al-'Attar, deputy prime minister and minister of industry; 
Dr. 'Abd-al-Karim al-Iryani, minister of planning and 
development; Brigadier General Yahya al-Mutwakkil, minister of 
interior; and Husayn al-Masiri, Sanaa mayor. 

