<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Musa Confirms 'Arafat, Peres, Christopher To Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2704144794 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1410 GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2704144794 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 27 Apr (MENA)--Foreign Minister 'Amr Musa has 
stated that Palestinian President Yasir 'Arafat will arrive in 
Cairo at midnight, Israeli Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres will 
arrive tomorrow morning, and U.S. Secretary of State Warren 
Christopher will arrive this evening. 
  Musa said a session of talks with the U.S. secretary of 
state 
will be held tomorrow morning. The talks will focus on the 
Middle East peace process and international issues of mutual 
interest. He added that President Mubarak will receive the 
three visitors in separate meetings tomorrow after the speech 
that he will deliver on workers' day. 
  Musa said Palestinian officials have informed him that the 
delegations to the Palestinian-Israeli talks have reached an 
agreement on most issues. He indicated that the Syrian track in 
the peace talks will be discussed tomorrow. 
  Musa said contacts are under way to arrange a meeting 
between 
Christopher, 'Arafat, and Peres. 

