<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reportage on Christopher, 'Arafat, Peres Visits </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reportage on Christopher, 'Arafat, Peres Visits </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Musa, Peres on Signing of Agreement </H4>

<F P=102> NC2804110494 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1035 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2804110494 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 28 Apr (MENA)--Foreign Minister 'Amr Musa has 
stated that there has been progress in the Palestinian-Israeli 
negotiations, contacts were made today, and others will be made 
when President Husni Mubarak receives U.S. Secretary of State 
Warren Christopher, Palestinian President Yasir 'Arafat, and 
Israeli Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres. 
  Speaking at a joint news conference with Peres following 
their talks here today, Musa said: Egypt is willing to host the 
signing of the agreement any time, and the date of its signing 
will be set very soon. 
  Shim'on Peres said: It will be possible to identify the 
remaining problems at the end of today's talks. We are still 
working to resolve the main points of dispute. We will set the 
date for signing the agreement when these issues are resolve. 
He added: If we reach an accord, then this agreement could be 
signed in an hour. But if there is no agreement, it might take 
a year. 
  Peres stressed that Egypt is playing a responsible and very 
wise role in the negotiating process and that there is no doubt 
the Middle East region is fortunate to have Egypt playing a 
role, one that we fully appreciate. 

</TEXT>

