<H3> <TI>   Five Journalists Dismissed; 'Udayy's Posts Listed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Five Journalists Dismissed; 'Udayy's Posts Listed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2804113494 London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT in Arabic 27 Apr 94 p2 </F>
<F P=103> PM2804113494 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "'Udayy Dismisses Five Journalists"] </F>
  [Text] Amman, AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT -- 'Udayy Saddam Husayn, 
son of the Iraqi president, has prevented five Iraqi journalists 
from exercising their profession and decided to dismiss them 
from the the Journalists Association he heads. Among these 
journalists are Lutfi al-Khayyat and Ahmad Sabri, both members 
of the association's council. The decision came the day after 
the announcement in the Iraqi press that 'Udayy had been chosen 
as chairman of the Youth Union. This is his latest post, as he 
also heads the Students Union, the Journalists Association, the 
Olympic Committee, the Football Association, and the cultural 
grouping supervising the Writers Union and the Artists Union. 
He also heads the Saddam Engineering College and supervises 
Baghdad University, al-Mustansiriyah University, the Saddam 
Medical College, and the Scientific Research Center. He is also 
chairman of the meat company in al-Dawrah and the meat company 
in al-Mahmudiyah. In addition to the declared 13 posts he also 
assumes undeclared political and security tasks. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

