  [Text] The National Assembly was informed today that 
Pakistan has thus far paid $658 million to the United States for 
the F-16 planes. In a written reply during the question hour, 
Defense Minister Aftab Shaban Mirani disclosed that the delivery 
of these aircraft to Pakistan was scheduled to begin in April 
1993, but the supply was stopped due to the Pressler Amendment. 
He said negotiations are under way with the U.S. Government on 
this issue. 

