<F P=100> Sri Lanka </F>
<H3> <TI>   Increase in External Assets Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Increase in External Assets Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2404115994 Colombo Sri Lanka Broadcasting Corporation 
International Service in English 1045 GMT 24 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2404115994 </F>
<F P=104>  Colombo Sri Lanka Broadcasting Corporation 
International Service </F>

<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sri Lanka's external assets rose substantially by 
$735 million. According to Central Bank statistics, the 
official reserve has also recorded an increase. This increase 
of $736 [as heard] million reflects the growing capital inflows 
and remittances. The country's foreign assets increased to 
2,298 million rupees by the end of February this year. The 
remittances of foreign expatriates have also recorded an 
increase of 16 percent. The tourist arrivals recorded an 
upsurge of four percent. 

</TEXT>

