<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Congress-I has said that India will not sign 
the Nonproliferation Treaty [NPT] unless all countries are 
included in it and it becomes nondiscriminatory in character. 
Talking to newspersons in New Delhi today, the party spokesman, 
Mr. V.N. Gadgil, said revision of the treaty is due next year 
and, therefore, member countries need to have some negotiations 
in this regard. 

</TEXT>

