<F P=100> India </F>
<H3> <TI>   Envoys Briefed on `Militant Activities' in Kashmir </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Envoys Briefed on `Militant Activities' in Kashmir </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2904082794 Delhi Doordarshan Television Network in English 
1630 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2904082794 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi Doordarshan Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The ambassadors of 11 countries currently on a 
four-day visit to Kashmir were yesterday briefed in Srinagar by 
senior Army officers about the Pak-sponsored militant activities 
in the valley. The ambassadors were told that the militants 
indulged in killing of innocent people, burned government and 
private property, and also misbehaved with women. Ambassadors 
of Peru, Egypt, Morocco, Tunisia, Kazakhstan, Kuwait, Iran, 
Argentina, Brazil, Jordan, and Oman were shown the arms and 
ammunition seized by the security forces during their 
anti-militant operations. 
  The ambassadors also met some foreign mercenaries who 
admitted that they were misled by false propaganda that a lot of 
atrocities were being committed on the Muslim population of the 
valley of Kashmir but when they came there they found that 
nothing of this sort was happening there. The militants said 
they were disappointed now. The ambassadors saw some wounded 
militants being treated by Army doctors. 
  The visiting ambassadors today called on the Jammu and 
Kashmir governor, Mr. K.V. Krishna Rao, at the Raj Bhavan. 

</TEXT>

