<F P=100> India </F>
<H3> <TI>   Two `Militants' Among 8 Killed in Kashmir </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Two `Militants' Among 8 Killed in Kashmir </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2904033794 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1430 
GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2904033794 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In the Kashmir valley, eight persons, including two 
militants and two political workers, were killed in the 
militancy-related incidents during the last 24 hours. Ghulam 
Qadir Janbaz, a National Conference worker, was shot dead by the 
militants at Vanabal and Mr. Abdus Salam Salar of 
Jamaat-i-Islami was killed at Nurbagh by the militants. 
Security forces arrested seven militants during search 
operation and recovered two AK rifles, three pistols, five 
grenades, one rocket launched, and a large quantity of 
ammunition. 
  Meanwhile, in Jammu and Kashmir, a vital suspension bridge 
over the Chenab near Loda was burned by the militants today. 
This has cut off a vital link to about 40 villages of Doda 
Tehsil near Jodhpur village. The bridge has been constructed 
about 25 years ago. 

</TEXT>

