<F P=100> India </F>
<H3> <TI>   Islamabad Reports on Strike in Kashmir </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Islamabad Reports on Strike in Kashmir </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2904032094 Islamabad PTV Television Network in English 
1400 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2904032094 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad PTV Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Complete strike was observed in occupied Kashmir 
today to protest against official hindrances in the way of 
people's contact with the visiting Islamic countries' 
ambassadors in the valley. All shops, business establishments, 
educational institutions, and private and public offices 
remained closed throughout the valley. Transport was completely 
off the road. A spokesman of the All Parties Hurriyat 
Conference accused the governor of not allowing the public 
access to the foreign envoys. 
  Meanwhile, another six people have been martyred and many 
injured in military crackdowns and clashes. Scores of youths 
were arrested during siege and search operations in different 
parts of the valley. 

</TEXT>

