<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Iraqi Envoy Conveys Message to President Ben Ali </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2704165594 Baghdad INA in Arabic 1313 GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN2704165594 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tunis, 27 Apr (INA)--On behalf of Tunisian President 
Zine El Abidine Ben Ali, Tunisian Prime Minister Hamed Karoui 
today received Barzan al-Tikriti, President Saddam Husayn's 
personal envoy. 
  During the meeting, Barzan al-Tikriti delivered a message 
from President Saddam Husayn to his brother Tunisian President 
Zine El Abidine Ben Ali. The message deals with the latest 
developments at the UN Security Council, Iraq's implementation 
of UN Security Council resolutions, the UN Security Council's 
obligations toward lifting the blockade, and the required 
inter-Arab coordination and consultation to achieve this 
objective. 
  The message also relays Iraq's stand on the current Arab 
situation, which requires that the leaf of the past be turned 
and Arab solidarity revived. 
  During the meeting, Hamed Karoui expressed the solidarity of 
the Tunisian leadership and people with Iraq. He stressed that 
Tunisia will spare no effort in the move to put an end to the 
suffering of the Iraqi people, especially since Iraq has 
implemented the relevant resolutions. 
  The Tunisian prime minister asked Barzan al-Tikriti to 
convey 
President Zine El Abidne Ben Ali's greetings to President Saddam 
Husayn. 

</TEXT>

