<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 28 Apr (MENA)--Israeli Foreign Minister 
Shim'on Peres has stated that the Israeli troops' withdrawal 
from the self-rule areas in Gaza and Jericho will take place the 
day after the implementation agreement is signed in Cairo. The 
agreement is scheduled to be signed on 4 May. 
  In an another development, Israeli diplomatic sources close 
to the intensive negotiations that were held in Cairo today have 
told MENA that the economic agreement between the PLO and Israel 
will be signed tomorrow, Friday, in Paris. The same sources 
pointed out that the signing will take place after all obstacles 
have been overcome. The agreement will be an integral part of 
the agreement for the implementation of self-rule in Gaza and 
Jericho. 

</TEXT>

