<F P=102>   LD2804214894 Algiers ENTV Television Network in Arabic 1900 
GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2804214894 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers ENTV Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] At the opening of the ordinary session of the 
Socialist Forces Front [FFS], the acting secretary-general 
stated that his party rejected any dialogue which did not aim at 
establishing democracy and human rights or did not conform to 
international values. During the session there was also talk 
about the Amazighi [Berber] and the national identity. Nasima 
Kirat reports: 
  [Kiratg] At FFS headquarters acting General Secretary 
Lounaoussi Hamid met veterans of the FFS. He directed his 
comments to the current situation the country is going through. 
  [Begin Lounaoussi recording] The FFS rejects violence as 
political means. The FFS rejects any agreement or settlement 
that could be reached between parties which advocate violence at 
the expense of democracy and the Algerian people. The FFS 
rejects any dialogue which does not aim at building an Algeria 
of democracy, an Algeria of Human rights, an Algeria that 
conforms with international values. [end recording] 
  [Kirat] He also spoke about the Amazighi cultural movement 
which continues, as he said, to advocate the Amazighi identity. 
[passage omitted] 

