  [Text] Cairo, 29 Apr (MENA)--Palestinian President Yasir 
'Arafat left Cairo for Tunis today after a two-day visit to 
Egypt. During the visit 'Arafat held talks with President Husni 
Mubarak, U.S. Secretary of State Warren Christopher, and Israeli 
Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres. The talks resulted in the 
fixing of 4 May as the target date for the signing in Cairo of 
the Palestinian-Israeli agreement on the implementation of 
self-rule in Gaza and Jericho. 
  'Arafat was seen off at the airport by Fatah Representative 
in Cairo Zuhdi al-Qidrah. 

