<H3> <TI>   Security Forces Arrest Killer of Police Captain </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Security Forces Arrest Killer of Police Captain </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2804174594 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1530 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2804174594 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 28 Apr (MENA)--Security men today arrested 
the killer of Captain Khalid Mustafa of the al-Hammam police 
force in Marsa Matruh, who was killed by a bullet last night. A 
security source in the Interior Ministry stated that defendant 
Fayiz Miftah Muhammad Sulayman admitted committing the crime and 
led the police to the weapon he used, an unregistered 
double-barreled hunting rifle. Capt. Khalid was killed and a 
police detective was injured in the shoot-out after they carried 
out a job arresting a defendant in the al-Hammam area in Marsa 
Matruh. The defendant was hunting in the area. When he saw the 
police force approaching, he tried to escape and during the 
chase he fired at the police force, killing Capt. Khalid and 
injuring a soldier. 

</TEXT>

