<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   People's Assembly Passes Foreign Exchange Law </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    People's Assembly Passes Foreign Exchange Law </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2704080594 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in 
Arabic 0500 GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2704080594 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The People's Assembly will resume its meetings today 
under the chairmanship of the speaker, Dr. Fathi Surur. In last 
night's session, the Assembly ratified the foreign currency 
bill. Under the new law, all individuals and corporations will 
be allowed to retain all their foreign currency earnings [rather 
than convert it into Egyptian pounds]. 
  Assembly members stressed that this law will boost 
confidence 
in the Egyptian economy, encourage foreign and domestic 
investment, and stimulate the national economy. 
  Mahmud Muhammad Mahmud, minister of economy and foreign 
trade, told the Assembly that the law will benefit both 
importers and exporters. The minister added that the $16 
billion that the Central Bank has in reserves measure the extent 
of the success of the country's economic policy. There is an 
oversupply of foreign exchange in Egypt and the new law will 
help bring about a balance between the supply and demand for 
foreign currency, Minister Mahmud stated. 

</TEXT>

