<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rwandan Trade Minister Arrives for Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rwandan Trade Minister Arrives for Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2804073494 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0615 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2804073494 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 28 Apr (MENA)--Rwanda's Trade, Industry, and 
Crafts Minister, Justin Mugenzi, arrived in Cairo early this 
morning on a visit to Egypt of several days. 
  The Rwandan minister said he would meet President Husni 
Mubarak, in his capacity as chairman of the OAU, to discuss the 
current critical situation in Rwanda following the death of 
Rwandan President Juvenal Habyarimana and the attacks carried 
out by the rebel Rwandan National Front. 
  The Rwandan minister said he would also explain to President 
Mubarak the failure to honor the Arusha Peace Agreement signed 
on 4 August 1993 and the violation of international accords and 
the principle of good-neighborliness by our neighboring state of 
Uganda. 
  He noted that what matters now is for the international 
public and the OAU to realize the role the Ugandan president is 
playing toward Rwanda and the extent of his material and moral 
influence. 
  The Rwandan president explained that he will brief President 
Mubarak on the UN role in supervising the implementation of the 
peace agreements in his country and will discuss the effects the 
UN Security Council resolutions will have on the UN mission in 
Rwanda. 
  He said he will seek President Mubarak's help to stop the 
violence and massacres in his country and restore stability and 
security. 

</TEXT>

