<H3> <TI>   `Fierce' Battles Reportedly Continue North of Sanaa </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Fierce' Battles Reportedly Continue North of Sanaa </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2804132894 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in 
Arabic 1230 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2804132894 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Political sources in Sanaa said today that fierce 
battles have resumed for the second consecutive day between 
Yemeni Army units positioned north of Sanaa. This fighting 
follows the collapse of the cease-fire declared last night. 
  According to the sources, heavy artillery and tanks are 
being 
used in the fighting between units loyal to President 'Ali 
'Abdallah Salih and units who support Vice President 'Ali Salim 
al-Bid. 
  Well-informed sources in Aden confirm the news of the 
fighting, saying that the southern forces, stationed north of 
Sanaa, are in control of the situation. These forces seized 30 
tanks belonging to the northern forces and destroyed 15 others, 
according to the same sources. 

</TEXT>

