<H3> <TI>   Further on Fighting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further on Fighting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2904072694 Paris Radio Monte Carlo in Arabic 0600 GMT 29 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2904072694 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris Radio Monte Carlo </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Independent sources have said that more than 100 
people have been killed and 200 others wounded in the clashes 
that took place in 'Imran, north of Sanaa, on Wednesday and 
Thursday [27 and 28 April] between the northern and southern 
armored units. 
  So far, no official count of casualties has been announced. 
Initial reports issued by the Defense Ministry in Sanaa noted 
that dozens of people, including civilians, were killed. The 
latest reports from Sanaa noted that artillery clashes and tank 
battles continued yesterday following the failure of the 
cease-fire reached Wednesday evening. Independent sources said 
that the southern forces were defeated in the battles, and 
consequently, the fighting abated yesterday afternoon. 
  These confrontations created severe tension in Sanaa. The 
anti-aircraft guns that provide protection for the airport and 
the Presidential Palace have been placed on alert. It was also 
reported that a boobytrapped car exploded near the residence of 
Shaykh 'Abdallah al-Ahmar, the speaker of the House of 
Representatives and leader of the Yemeni Reform Grouping, but no 
casualties were reported. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

