<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Gunmen Attempt To Assassinate Deputy Prime Minister </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Gunmen Attempt To Assassinate Deputy Prime Minister </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2804204194 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
2000 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2804204194 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] An official security source at the Interior Ministry 
has told the Yemeni News Agency, SABA', that at 1345 today 
brother Dr. Hasan Muhammad Makki, the first deputy prime 
minister, was the target of a sinful assassination attempt. 
According to initial investigations, five attackers driving two 
Toyota cars blocked the path of the brother first deputy prime 
minister's car as it was driving along (?al-Mathar) Street in 
front of the Ministry of Local Administration. They opened fire 
on his car with automatic weapons, wounding him in the shoulder 
and leg. Three of his escorts were fatally wounded. The 
brother Dr. Hgasan Makki was rushed to hospital, where he has 
been receiving treatment and is now in satisfactory condition. 
  Security forces captured the attackers, who are now being 
questioned. 
  The source expressed deep regret over this deplorable 
incident. He called on all citizens to exercise alertness, 
awareness and restraint to forestall seditions in society. He 
called for their cooperation to help security agencies fulfill 
their functions under the critical circumstances our Yemeni 
homeland is experiencing. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

