<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   House of Representatives Discusses Events in 'Imran </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    House of Representatives Discusses Events in 'Imran </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2804130094 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1200 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2804130094 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The House of Representatives held an extraordinary 
meeting this morning under the chairmanship of Shaykh 'Abdallah 
Bin-Husayn al-Ahmar, the House speaker. Discussions centered on 
developments resulting from the country's political crisis, the 
latest of which are the events that took place in 'Imran. 
  The House told its committee, which includes members of the 
Defense and Security Committee, as well as a number of deputies, 
to immediately begin a fact-finding mission in 'Imran and other 
problem areas, and to present a comprehensive and urgent report 
to the House. 
  The House heard a number of proposals on these developments 
and assigned the House speakership and leaders of parliamentary 
blocs to issue a House statement in light of proposals and ideas 
that were presented at the meeting. 
  We will broadcast the House statement later this evening. 
The House of Representatives will continue its meetings next 
Monday, God willing. 

</TEXT>

