<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Salih Receives Envoy, Message From Egypt's Mubarak </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Salih Receives Envoy, Message From Egypt's Mubarak </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2904054894 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
0430 GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2904054894 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brother Lieutenant General 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, 
chairman of the Presidential Council, last night received 
brother Badr Hammam, Egyptian assistant foreign minister and the 
envoy of Egyptian President Muhammad Husni Mubarak. Hammam 
conveyed to the brother president a message from his brother 
President Muhammad Husni Mubarak. The message deals with 
developments in our region and the efforts exerted by the 
brothers in Egypt to contain the political crisis and to end its 
regrettable repercussions, especially on the media and military 
levels. 
  The message also expresses the Egyptian president's concern 
over the regrettable incidents that took place at the 'Imran 
camp. The message stresses Egypt's concern about security and 
stability and about supporting the march of unity and democracy 
in our country and exerting all efforts to achieve this. 
  The brother president asked the Egyptian envoy to convey a 
reply to his brother Egyptian President Muhammad Husni Mubarak 
reassuring him about the situation in our country. In his 
message, the brother president expresses his eagerness to exert 
every effort required to guarantee the safety of the Yemeni 
homeland and to foil all schemes aimed at threatening the march 
of security, stability, unity, and democracy in our country. 
The message also expresses the brother president's deep 
appreciation for the efforts of the brothers in Egypt, 
especially his brother President Muhammad Husni Mubarak, to 
prevent the danger of conflicts and violence in our country and 
to support the march of Yemeni unity since it is a national and 
pan-Arab gain that cannot be relinquished at any price. 
  The meeting was attended by 'Atta' Hardun, the Egyptian 
ambassador to our country. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

