<F P=100> Sudan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-Bashir Addresses Citizens, Grants Amnesty </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Bashir Addresses Citizens, Grants Amnesty </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA2804212794 Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network in 
Arabic 2245 GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA2804212794 </F>
<F P=104>  Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Lieutenant General 'Umar Hasan Ahmad al-Bashir, 
president of the Republic, has said that the enemies of Islam 
and the revolution meet abroad and incite the colonialists to 
invade Sudan. He called on the sons of the homeland to prepare 
to defend it. During his address yesterday in al-Mujlad town, 
in Western Kordofan State, Lt. Gen. 'Umar said the banner of 
Islam has risen in Sudan, pointing out the [word indistinct] of 
the imam al-Mahdi. He promised the masses to contribute to the 
success of the missionary activity project and agricultural 
projects to strengthen development. 
  His excellency also issued a decree granting amnesty to all 
those who were involved in the incidents of the Misiriyyah and 
Zuyud [tribal clashes] and he received the reconciliation 
document concerning this issue. 

