<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Officials Deny `Majdal Shams First' Proposal </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Officials Deny `Majdal Shams First' Proposal </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2904114894 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1100 GMT 29 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2904114894 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Residents of the Druze settlements on the Golan 
Heights are saying they have learned from various sources in 
Syria that U.S. Secretary of State Warren Christopher will 
deliver an Israeli proposal to Damascus entitled Majdal Shams 
First. The proposal suggests that during the first stage, Syria 
be given sovereignty and control over the four Druze settlements 
on the Golan Heights. 
  Our correspondents Nati Zilberman and Hayim Hecht report 
that 
the Druze villagers on the Golan Heights are already preparing 
for such a possibility. 
  Officials at the Prime Minister's Office, at the Foreign 
Ministry, and in the IDF [Israel Defense Forces] denied any 
plans for a withdrawal from Majdal Shams first. Our 
correspondents nevertheless report that the maps prepared by the 
General Staff contain several possible options for the transfer 
of the Druze villages to Syrian control. 

</TEXT>

