<H3> <TI>   IDF Sources on Importance of Hamas-Fatah Agreement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    IDF Sources on Importance of Hamas-Fatah Agreement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2904051594 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0400 GMT 29 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2904051594 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Senior IDF [Israel Defense Forces] sources said 
that Hamas [Islamic Resistance Movement] and Fatah have moved 
closer together recently. This process is important and 
consequential for Israel as well. The sources said that the 
rapprochement between the two organizations came against the 
background of Hamas attempts to share control of the autonomy 
institutions. 
  The understandings between the two organizations were 
reached 
in a bid to reduce internecine fighting during the sensitive 
period when the Palestinians assume authority over the 
autonomous areas. The sources attribute great importance to the 
prevention of internecine fighting between the two organizations 
and say that an agreement between them could lead to a reduction 
in terrorism and violence in the Gaza Strip. 

</TEXT>

