<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Army Approves 10 Armed Bodyguards for Fatah Leaders </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Army Approves 10 Armed Bodyguards for Fatah Leaders </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2604174494 Tel Aviv 'AL HAMISHMAR in Hebrew 26 Apr 94 pp 
1, 8 </F>

<F P=103> TA2604174494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv 'AL HAMISHMAR </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Aharon Klein] </F>
  [Text] Some 10 armed bodyguards have been recently 
assigned to protect Fatah leaders in the Gaza Strip. The step 
had been approved by the IDF [Israel Defense Forces] and the 
defense establishment. The bodyguards received personal 
handguns, which had been purchased by Palestinians after 
receiving special Israeli approval. The decision to approve the 
employment of armed bodyguards was made in the wake of an 
explicit Palestinian request. In discussions with senior IDF 
officers, senior Fatah officials explained they had to protect 
themselves against assassination attempts by peace-opposing 
organizations. 
  The defense establishment's approval was granted on the 
strict condition that the bodyguards should only fire for 
protection and that they would not exhibit their weapons in 
public. The bodyguards have been issued appropriate permits. 
It should be noted that before the handguns were handed to the 
bodyguards, they were registered and ballistically tested. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

