<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   New Commander Suspends Activity of IDF Squads </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New Commander Suspends Activity of IDF Squads </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2704112494 Tel Aviv HA'ARETZ in Hebrew 27 Apr 94 p A1 </F>
<F P=103> TA2704112494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv HA'ARETZ </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by military correspondent Eytan Rabin] </F>
  [Text] Major General Ilan Biran, commander of the IDF 
[Israel Defense Forces] Central Command, has ordered suspension 
of the activity of the squads operating against stone throwers 
in the West Bank. These squads were set up during the tenure of 
Major General Nehemya Tamari in order to apprehend stone 
throwers, including opening fire when necessary. The squads 
operated for several months, until the military advocate-general 
sent a letter instructing clarification of the orders relating 
to their operation. 
  The activity of the squads was resumed when Major General 
Dani Yatom was appointed temporary commander of the Central 
Command, and was occasionally halted on the basis of operational 
considerations. Major General Sha'ul Mufaz, commander of the IDF 
forces in the West Bank, renewed the activity of the squads 
several months ago. Maj. Gen. Biran ordered to suspend their 
operation several days after he entered office. 
  Central Command sources said Maj. Gen. Biran implemented 
this 
move in order to avoid unnecessary firing. They said Biran is 
checking all the standing orders relating to the Central 
Command, mainly open-fire orders, issued during the tenures of 
Yatom and Tamari. 
  An army source said "Biran is examining every order given in 
the Central Command and canceling those he does not approve of." 
If necessary, Biran will issue out new instructions. 
  The military sources add that Maj. Gen. Biran has held 
meetings with the Central Command's senior officers, including 
the division and brigade commanders, and visited the sensitive 
areas of the West Bank in order to get personally acquainted 
with the various spheres relating to his new post. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-14331 </DOCNO>
