<H3> <TI>   Detentions of Oppositionists in Strip Continues </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Detentions of Oppositionists in Strip Continues </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2904112494 Tel Aviv YEDI'OT AHARONOT in Hebrew 29 Apr 94 p 
6 </F>

<F P=103> TA2904112494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv YEDI'OT AHARONOT </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by David Regev] </F>
  [Excerpt] The wave of detentions against opponents of the 
peace process in the Gaza Strip continues. Twenty-five Hamas 
[Islamic Resistance Movement] and Islamic Jihad activists in the 
Strip were arrested over the past 24 hours by the security 
forces, Arab sources reported yesterday. 
  According to the sources, the activists were detained in 
their homes and the security forces also visited the homes of 15 
activists and fugitives who were not at home, and demanded their 
relatives give them up. Among those detained were Shaykh Nafar 
A'zam, 40, of Rafah, an Islamic Jihad leader who was put under 
administrative detention for six months. A'zam was released 
several weeks ago after a long period of imprisonment. 
  A senior activist of the Popular Front for the Liberation of 
Palestine, Walid al-Rul, 40, of al-Shati', was put under 
administrative detention for six months for the ninth time. 
Arab sources said he has been under detention for 53 months 
running. 
  Khalil Bal'awi, 24, a Hamas wanted man, was captured by 
security forces in Gaza yesterday. Bal'awi is suspected of 
terrorist activity against the security forces, including firing 
at IDF [Israel Defense Forces] patrols. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

