<H3> <TI>   Poll Conducted on Uprooting Settlements for Peace </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Poll Conducted on Uprooting Settlements for Peace </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2904105794 Tel Aviv YEDI'OT AHARONOT in Hebrew 29 Apr 94 p 
1 </F>

<F P=103> TA2904105794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv YEDI'OT AHARONOT </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Poll by the Dafah Institute headed by Dr. Mina Zemah] </F>
  [Text] The prime minister said: "Peace is more important 
for Israel's future and security than this or that group of 
settlements." Do you agree or disagree with that statement? 
  Agree: 51 percent; Disagree: 45 percent; No comment: 4 
percent. 
  The prime minister continued: "I supported and will continue 
to support the removal of Golan settlements for the sake of 
peace." Do you agree or disagree with that position? 
  Agree: 39 percent; Disagree: 58 percent; No comment: 3 
percent. 
  In your opinion, should the prime minister have made those 
remarks in public? 
  Should have: 50 percent; Should not have: 47 percent; No 
comment: 
  3 percent. 
  The poll was conducted on Tuesday and Wednesday among 547 
interviewees, which make up a representative example of the 
adult population. Maximum margin of error is 4 percent. 

</TEXT>

