<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Memorandum Signed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Memorandum Signed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2704140694 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1100 GMT 27 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2704140694 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Israel and China signed a memorandum of 
understanding to cooperate in the energy field. Our 
correspondent Arye Schorr reports that Israel might buy coal in 
China for the Israel Electricity Corporation and an experimental 
shipment will arrive here within several days. 
  China is interested in technology to produce electricity 
from 
solar energy and from oil shale developed in Israel, as well as 
cooperation with a cable company to manufacture electricity 
cables in China. The memorandum was signed by Energy Minister 
Moshe Shahal and the Chinese electric power industry minister, 
who is visiting Israel. 

</TEXT>

