<H3> <TI>   Hajj Official Criticizes Saudi Stand </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hajj Official Criticizes Saudi Stand </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2904100994 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 0930 GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2904100994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hojjat ol-Eslam val-Moslemin Mohammad Reyshahri, the 
representative of the esteemed leader and the supervisor of the 
Iranian pilgrims to the House of God [Mecca] stressed: The 
disavowal of infidels is a part of the hajj, is the spirit of 
the hajj and is the true meaning of this great congress. 
  The supervisor of the Iranian pilgrims to the House of God, 
who was speaking before today's Friday prayers sermons in 
Tehran, criticized the approach of the Saudi Arabian Government 
towards the disavowal of infidels ceremonies and said: We are 
not trying to create any disturbances for the Saudi Government. 
However, on the basis of Islamic principles and at the urging 
of the guardian of the cause of Muslims [Khamene'i], and in 
order to implement a divine injunction, we will perform these 
ceremonies. 
  He said: In Islam it is incumbent upon people to take part 
in the disavowal of infidels ceremonies. He added: To separate 
the political dimension from the hajj means that in this great 
congress the Muslims will have to do nothing regarding the 
enemies of Islam and should not find any solutions for the 
political and social problems in Islamic countries, including in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina, which is burning in the fire of Serbian 
atrocities. 
  He urged Saudi officials not to prevent the Muslims from 
carrying out their duty in performing the disavowal of infidels 
ceremonies in this year's hajj pilgrimage. 

</TEXT>

