<H3> <TI>   Mali President, Delegation Arrives for Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Mali President, Delegation Arrives for Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2804213094 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 1930 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2804213094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Mr. Alpha Oumar Konare, president of Mali, arrived 
in Tehran a few moments ago and Mr. Habibi, first vice 
president, welcomed him. Here is our correspondent with a 
report: 
  [Correspondent] Mr. Alpha Oumar Konare, Mali president, 
arrived in Tehran a few moments ago at the head of a delegation 
and was officially welcomed by First Vice President Mr. Habibi. 
  On arrival in Tehran, the Mali president said he considers 
the expansion of friendly and fraternal relations with the 
Iranian nation and government to be very important and seeks to 
hold talks with Iranian officials on expansion of ties, as well 
as on regional and world issues. 
  He added: The cooperation and mutual understanding between 
the two Muslim countries is most crucial under present world 
conditions and considering the new world order. 
  Mr. Habibi, our country's first vice president, referring to 
the priority of ties with Muslim and African states in the 
Islamic Republic of Iran's [IRI] foreign policy said: Taking 
into consideration the ancient history of the state of Mali and 
the influence of Islam in that country, Iran wishes to expand 
its cooperation with that country and during the visit the 
expansion of economic and cultural ties will be discussed. 
  The first round of talks between the two presidents of IRI 
and Mali will be held in Tehran tomorrow morning. 

</TEXT>

