<H3> <TI>   Meets Hashemi-Rafsanjani </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Meets Hashemi-Rafsanjani </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2904103794 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 0930 GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2904103794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In a meeting with Malian President Alpha Oumar 
Konare, President Hashemi-Rafsanjani placed emphasis on the 
Islamic Republic of Iran's foreign policy which stresses 
cooperation with African countries in general and Muslim 
countries in particular. 
  During this morning's meeting, the president of Mali 
expressed pleasure about visiting Iran. He pointed out that 
unity among Muslim and other nations plays an effective role in 
the resolution of world problems, and called for the expansion 
of relations with Iran. He added: Your excellency is well aware 
of the situation in African countries and particularly in Mali, 
as well as the problems of that continent, and I feel that I am 
able to hold discussions with your excellency in all fields. 
  In response, Hashemi-Rafsanjani thanked Mr. Konare for his 
sincere remarks and referred to Iran's foreign policy, giving 
priority to cooperation with Muslim countries and said: We are 
ready for extensive cooperation with the Muslim and friendly 
country of Mali in all fields of interest to the two countries. 
He added: Your country can be a powerful country in 
agriculture and animal husbandry, and your plentiful natural 
resources can play a decisive role in solving your country's 
problems. Underdevelopment there should be seen as an outcome 
of the colonialism which dominated your country for years. The 
president said: We hope that you succeed in overcoming your 
problems through your work and through solidarity now that you 
are independent. We in Iran had some good experiences and are 
ready to cooperate with you, and Islam, which is the common bond 
between the two countries, can play a significant role in ever 
expanding cooperation. 
  Also during the meeting, the problems of the Islamic world, 
particularly problems of Palestine and Bosnia-Herzegovina, were 
discussed and the two sides stressed the need for further 
solidarity among Islamic countries in order to solve problems of 
the Muslim people of Bosnia-Herzegovina. 

</TEXT>

