<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Deputy Foreign Minister, Philippine Envoy View Ties </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Deputy Foreign Minister, Philippine Envoy View Ties </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2604190794 Tehran IRNA in English 1841 GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2604190794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, April 26, IRNA -- The Philippine ambassador 
here, Oscar Valenzuela and First Deputy Foreign Minister 
Mohammad Hashemi, on Tuesday discussed the holding of the 
Tehran-Manila joint economic commission. 
  The two sides agreed that the commission was an ideal forum 
to improve bilateral relations and explore avenues of 
cooperation. 
  Valenzuela called for further expansion of bilateral 
relations and cooperation in light of the economic potential of 
the two countries. 
  Hashemi suggested that cooperation between regional 
organizations such as the Economic Cooperation Organization 
(ECO) and the Association of South East Asian Nations (ASEAN), 
would prove useful to both sides. 
  Philippine is a member of the ASEAN which also includes 
Brunei, Indonesia, Malaysia, Singapore and Thailand, while Iran 
is a founding member of the 10-nation ECO, whose other members 
are Pakistan, Turkey, Afghanistan, Tajikistan, Azerbaijan, 
Kazakhstan, Kyrgyzstan, Uzbekistan and Turkmenistan. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

