<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Emphasizes Islamic Values in Speech </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President Emphasizes Islamic Values in Speech </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2704182194 Tehran IRIB Television First Program Network in 
Persian 1630 GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2704182194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRIB Television First Program Network </F>
<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Hashemi-Rafsanjani, in a gathering of the 
central council of the Islamic Coalition Society 
[ICS--Jam'iyyat-e Mo'talefe-ye Eslami], described action based 
on the axis of velayat-e faqih [guardianship of the 
jurisconsult] and following the guidelines of the exalted 
leadership [Khamene'i] at this juncture in society to be a duty 
for officials, the people, and various formations of the 
community. 
  Praising the lofty character of the martyrs of ICS, the 
president said: What guarantees the correctness and soundness 
of the activities of a formation is its adherence to the 
principle of velayat-e faqih and giving preference to the 
interests of the Islamic system as opposed to personal and 
factional interests. The ICS has maintained its adherence to 
that important principle since its inception. 
  Referring to the fact that Iran is known as a wealthy state 
in the world, Hashemi-Rafsanjani laid emphasis on the need for 
endeavor, planning, and sincere cooperation among each and every 
one of the people and said: Thus, we will prove to the world 
that a nation is able to make up for past underdevelopment and 
to correct past wrongful policies through reliance on its 
financial and human resources while preserving its holy, 
Islamic, noble, and national values and aspirations. The 
realization of that import by the end of the second development 
plan is not hard to expect. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

