<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Central Bank Governor, IMF's Camdessus Confer </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Central Bank Governor, IMF's Camdessus Confer </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2804083494 Tehran IRNA in English 0536 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2804083494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, April 28, IRNA -- The governor of Iran's 
Central Bank Mohammad Hoseyn 'Adeli in a meeting with the 
managing director of International Monetary Fund, Michel 
Camdessus, in Washington D.C. Tuesday exchanged views on the 
issues of mutual interest. 'Adeli briefed Camdessus on the 
achievements and progress of the first development plan saying 
that during the first five-year development plan Iran's gross 
domestic product (GDP) has considerably increased. Despite 
pressures from some foreign countries, Iran has succeeded in 
concluding useful agreements with its trade partners, 'Adeli 
said. 
  Camdessus said that Iran's success in rescheduling its 
foreign debts would increase its credit in the fields of trade 
and commerce. He also lauded Iran's stands vis-a-vis the 
developing countries. 
  'Adeli is currently in Washington D.C. to attend the joint 
session of the World Bank and International Monetary Fund. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

