<H3> <TI>   Cabinet Decides To Sell Off Government Vehicles </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cabinet Decides To Sell Off Government Vehicles </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2704205694 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 1930 GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2704205694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] The cabinet held a session on Wednesday [27 
April] night. At the end of the session the first 
vice-president and the government spokesman, Mr. Habibi, 
announced: According to operational regulations adopted by the 
cabinet all government vehicles will be released from government 
control and sold off to natural and corporate persons on an 
instalment basis. 
  He added: Those public servants who wish to take early 
retirement or form a cooperative will be able to purchase 
government vehicles. He said: 20 percent of the vehicles 
belonging to the government must be sold off by the end of the 
year [ending 20 March 1995] according to a decision by the 
Islamic Consultative Majlis. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

