<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Talks With Jordanian Transportation Companies End </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2804110694 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 2015 GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2804110694 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Minutes of meetings held by the General Assembly of 
the Syrian-Jordanian Maritime Navigation Company and the General 
Assembly of the Syrian-Jordanian Land Transport Company were 
signed at the Ministry of Transportation this evening. 
  The minutes were signed for the Syrian side by Minister of 
Transportation Dr. Mufid 'Abd-al-Karim and for the Jordanian 
side by Minister of Transport Adib Halasah. 
  After the signing, Dr. 'Abd-al-Karim announced the 
conclusion 
of the meetings. He said that the two companies are true 
witnesses of the importance of joint Arab action which President 
Hafiz al-Asad and King Husayn support and seek to achieve, 
develop, and entrench for the benefit of all the Arabs. 
  For his part, Jordanian Transport Minister Adib Halasah 
expressed his hopes to continue joint action and wished the 
people in Syria and Jordan continuous growth and strength under 
the leaderships of President Hafiz al-Asad and King Husayn. 

</TEXT>

