<F P=100> Inter-Arab Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Arab League Urges Yemenis To Resolve Differences </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Arab League Urges Yemenis To Resolve Differences </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2804163694 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1320 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2804163694 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 28 Apr (MENA)--The Arab League Secretariat 
General expressed its deep concern over the military 
confrontation in Yemen which is threatening its unity, security, 
and stability and subjecting the constant Arab efforts to find a 
solution for the crisis to failure. 
  In a statement issued today, the Arab League appealed to all 
the Yemeni parties to exercise self-restraint, unite their 
ranks, resolve their differences through frankness and dialogue, 
and abide by what was agreed on in the Pledge and Agreement 
Document signed by the Yemeni brothers in the Jordanian capital, 
Amman, on 20 February 1994. 
  The statement stressed that Yemen's unity is a "national 
gain 
and a pan-Arab achievement" that should be protected in order to 
establish stability and security in Yemen in particular and the 
region in general. 
  It reiterated the need for all the Yemeni parties to protect 
the state of unity and overcome all the obstacles and 
difficulties that are impeding the attainment of national accord. 
  The statement declared the Arab League Secretariat General's 
readiness to mobilize all its resources in order to help remove 
the specter of civil war in fraternal Yemen. 

</TEXT>

