<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   PLO `Discussing National Authority'; Hurani Returns </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PLO `Discussing National Authority'; Hurani Returns </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2804114294 London AL-HAYAH in Arabic 27 Apr 94 p 5 </F>
<F P=103> PM2804114294 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-HAYAH </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Rashid Khashanah: "Hurani Returns to the PLO </F>
Executive Committee; Palestinian Leadership Discussing National 
Authority Structure"] 
  [Excerpts] Tunis -- Informed Palestinian sources in Tunis 
have told AL-HAYAH that the PLO leadership is currently 
discussing the structure of the Palestinian national authority 
to agree on a final formula before submitting it to the 
Israelis. They added that the discussions have so far resulted 
in agreement to have figures from inside the occupied territory 
and figures from the diaspora equally represented in the 
authority body. [passage omitted] 
  Meanwhile, informed Palestinian sources have stated that 
'Abdallah Hurani, who had resigned from the PLO Executive 
Committee, has had a reconciliation with President Yasir 
'Arafat. Their reconciliation resulted in his appointment as 
head of the "Returnees Department" formerly headed by 
'Abd-al-Rahim Malluh, the representatiave of the Popular Front 
for the Liberation of Palestine [PFLP] in the Executive 
Committee (who had also resigned). 
  Hurani, who, along with five other Executive Committee 
members, resigned after the Palestinian-Israeli Declaration of 
Principles was signed on 13 September 1993, was previously head 
of the PLO's Cultural Department. 
  AL-HAYAH has learned that Malluh visited Tunis at the end of 
last week for the first time since resigning from the Executive 
Committee last September. He met with some prominent Fatah 
leaders and also probably met with President 'Arafat. This is 
considered to be the first meeting between the the PFLP and 
Fatah since the Declaration of Principles was signed. 

</TEXT>

