<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Self-Rule Authority Formed, Headed By 'Arafat </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Self-Rule Authority Formed, Headed By 'Arafat </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2804144694 Jerusalem AL-QUDS in Arabic 28 Apr 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> TA2804144694 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem AL-QUDS </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, QUDS PRESS -- Informed Palestinian sources 
have said that the PLO leadership recently completed the 
formation of the national authority that will manage the 
self-government's affairs in the Gaza Strip and the Jericho area 
in accordance with the Palestinian-Israeli Declaration of 
Principles. 
  According to the Palestinian sources, who are close to the 
Cairo talks, Palestinian President Yasir 'Arafat will personally 
head this authority, which will be announced at a later date. 
  The sources, who wished to remain anonymous, linked the 
announcement on the formation of this authority to the 
achievement of fundamental progress that ensures the 
Palestinians the beginning of the implementation of the 
Declaration of Principles. 
  The Palestinian sources told QUDS PRESS that "Israel's 
procrastination and its non-adherence to dates on which 
agreement had been reached forced the Palestinian leadership to 
postpone the announcement on the national authority's formation." 
  The Palestinian sources refused to provide details on the 
formation of this body but said that it will comprise 18 
members, 11 from the diaspora and seven from the occupied 
territories. The distribution of the authority's diaspora 
members will be as follows: Seven from the PLO Executive 
Committee, two from the Fatah Central Committee, and two 
independents. 
  The Israeli Government had called on the Palestinian 
leadership to announce the self-rule authority, but the PLO 
rejected this demand as premature. The Palestinian sources 
expressed the belief that the announcement on the formation of 
the authority might provoke internal conflicts, especially as 
there is no Palestinian authority inside the occupied 
territories to impose the law. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

