<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Asks Negotiators To Open `Martyrs' Files </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Arafat Asks Negotiators To Open `Martyrs' Files </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2604093894 Sanaa Voice of Palestine in Arabic 1800 GMT 25 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2604093894 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Voice of Palestine </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brother Abu-'Ammar [Yasir 'Arafat], president of the 
state of Palestine and chairman of the PLO Executive Committee, 
has asked Palestinian negotiators to open the file of the 
Palestinian martyrs who fell during confrontations with the 
Israeli occupation troops during the period of armed fedayeen 
action that was launched from Jordanian, Syrian, and Lebanese 
territories, in addition to the occupied territories. 
  Palestinian sources said that the Israeli authorities have 
been holding the bodies of more than 100 martyrs in morgues for 
over two decades, and that they refuse to hand them to their 
families. The sources explained that this request was passed on 
during the meetings that were held in Tunis over the past two 
days. 

</TEXT>

