  [Text] Brother President Abu-'Ammar [Yasir 'Arafat] has 
received a letter from British Prime Minister John Major, in 
response to a letter from 'Arafat on the obstacles preventing 
the implementation of the PLO-Israeli agreement and the 
withdrawal from Gaza and Jericho. 
  In his letter, Mr. Major stressed that the United Kingdom 
would continue to give its full support for the peace process. 
He said: We and our partners within the European Union are 
prepared use our means to help politically and financially. 

