<F P=103> TA2604150594 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem AL-NAHAR </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Informed Palestinian sources have said that 
Damascus refused to receive Palestinian President Yasir 
'Arafat's envoy, whom he dispatched last week in an attempt to 
improve Syria's relationship with the chairman of the PLO 
Executive Committee. 
  'Arafat's envoy, who is a member of the PLO Executive 
Committee and who arrived unexpectedly in Damascus, returned 
without achieving anything because of the Syrian officials' 
refusal to receive him. 
  It has been learned that 'Arafat's envoy met Khalid 
al-Fahum, 
head of the Salvation Front, but nothing has been reported about 
what transpired at this meeting. 
  The PLO Executive Committee member who visited Damascus has 
reportedly said that he did not have a mission of reconciliation 
between the Syrian president and 'Arafat but that he traveled 
there "to perform a social duty." 

