<H3> <TI>   Fatah Invites Factions to National Dialogue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fatah Invites Factions to National Dialogue </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2604150794 Jerusalem AL-NAHAR in Arabic 24 Apr 94 pp 1, 7 </F>
<F P=103> TA2604150794 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem AL-NAHAR </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By 'Abd-al-Ra'uf Arna'ut] </F>
  [Excerpt] Jerusalem -- AL-NAHAR has learned that an 
internal dialogue among Palestinian factions that support and 
oppose the Palestinian-Israeli agreement is currently taking 
place inside and outside the occupied territories. The aim of 
this dialogue is to reach a draft joint agreement on unity in 
view of the conditions that will prevail in the occupied 
territories during the coming stage. 
  Fatah has invited all Palestinian political and militant 
forces to a comprehensive national dialogue. The invitation, 
extended by Ahmad Ghunaym, head of Fatah's office in Jerusalem, 
during a commemorative ceremony for martyr Khalil al-Wazir, 
said: We invite our brothers in Hamas [Islamic Resistance 
Movement], the Islamic Jihad, the Popular Front for the 
Liberation of Palestine, the People's Party, FIDA [Palestinian 
Democratic Union], and all our national movements to a 
comprehensive dialogue in order to affirm that this homeland 
does not belong to one organization but to the entire people. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

