<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fatah's Zaki Praises Agreement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fatah's Zaki Praises Agreement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2604184694 Jerusalem AL-QUDS in Arabic 24 Apr 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> TA2604184694 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem AL-QUDS </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By 'Izzat Daraghmah] </F>
  [Excerpt] Jerusalem -- In the first Palestinian reaction 
to the agreement between Fatah and Hamas [Islamic Resistance 
Movement], Fatah Central Committee member 'Abbas Zaki said that 
this agreement affirms the futility of betting on Palestinian 
division and weakness. The agreement will lead to a unified and 
good performance that will enable us to look forward to a good 
future. Moreover, it will constitute the groundwork for 
expanding the circle of dialogue and finalizing formulas for 
Palestinian unity. 
  In an exclusive statement, Zaki added: This is the first 
time in history that the Palestinians have embarked on 
establishing an entity. That requires priority in caring for, 
protecting, and defending this entity. 
  Zaki stressed: In order to avoid what happened in other 
revolutions that ended painfully with the outbreak of civil 
wars, we will not allow those models to be repeated in 
Palestine. Therefore, we have continued and will continue the 
dialogue with all Islamic and national Palestinian forces and 
factions in a bid to avoid the specter of a civil war and 
infighting. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

