<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Khamis Splits From PFLP-GC; Jibril Aide `Surprised' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Khamis Splits From PFLP-GC; Jibril Aide `Surprised' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2804160094 London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT in Arabic 28 Apr 94 94 
p 5 </F>

<F P=103> LD2804160094 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Salwa al-Ustuwani: "Khamis Confirms Split From </F>
`General Command'"] 
  [Excerpt] Damascus, Amman, London, AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT -- 
Mustafa Khamis, a Popular Front for the Liberation of 
Palestine--General Command [PFLP-GC] leader, has confirmed his 
split from the Front and the formation of a new command under 
his leadership called the Popular Front for the Liberation of 
Palestine--Islamic General Command. 
  In a statement to AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT in his residence in 
Amman 
yesterday Khamis said that he has taken this step in protest at 
the attitude of the Front's leadership, saying that he had, on 
several occasions, asked the Front's Central Committee to form a 
special committee to investigate the accusations leveled at him 
by some officials in order to judge them and expel them from its 
ranks. But his requests fell on deaf ears and, as a result, some 
Central Committee members conspired against him and hence 
dismissed him as official in charge of the General Command on 
the Jordanian scene and action in the western sector of the 
occupied territories. 
  However, circles of the PFLP-GC led by Ahmad Jibril were 
surprised by these reports when AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT went to ask 
them about the causes that led to the split. 
  General Command officials expressed their astonishment at 
and 
rejection of the idea. An employee in Jibril's office told 
AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT that it is a personal action, and the 
Palestinian issue does not need further splits and 
fragmentation. Such actions harm Palestinian struggle, which he 
is working to unify in order to confront the Israeli enemy, his 
practices, and his agreement with Palestinian President Yasir 
'Arafat. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

