<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Palestinian, Israeli Negotiators Resume Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Palestinian, Israeli Negotiators Resume Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2804153094 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1300 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2804153094 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 28 Apr (MENA)--The Palestinian and Israeli 
negotiators today resumed their talks on the implementation of 
the Gaza-Jericho agreement. 
  Palestinian sources said that the security and legal 
committees stemming from the negotiations are now formulating 
the points agreed on during the talks held in the past few days 
and trying to resolve issues that have not yet been resolved. 
  The sources added that the negotiators are waiting for the 
outcome of Palestinian President Yasir 'Arafat's talks with 
Israeli Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres and U.S. Secretary of 
State Warren Christopher and also the outcome of Presidents 
'Arafat and Husni Mubarak's talks, which will have direct 
bearing on overcoming the disputed points between the 
Palestinians and Israelis. 
  The sources expect the two sides to reach an agreement next 
week on implementing the Gaza-Jericho agreement in preparation 
for the signing of the agreement by Palestinian President 
'Arafat and Israeli Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin under President 
Husni Mubarak's auspices. 

</TEXT>

