<F P=100> ARAB AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Algeria </F>
<H3> <TI>   Prime Minister Sifi Meets With Local Officials </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Prime Minister Sifi Meets With Local Officials </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2804155494 Algiers Radio Algiers Network in Arabic 1200 
GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2804155494 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Radio Algiers Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] This morning the head of government, Prime Minister 
Mokdad Sifi, met with the representatives of four pilot 
municipalities in his office. The representatives were chosen 
from the Governorates of Algiers, Batna, Sidi Bel Abbes, and 
Illizi. 
  The meeting was the first of its kind. It was attended by 
the minister of interior and localities as well as by a number 
of governors. The meeting is an opportunity to come closer to 
the real problems facing municipalities. 
  Also, this meeting would be an opportunity to put the last 
touches on his government's program, due to be announced in the 
next few days, by drawing on the citizen's concerns and problems 
in deprived municipalities. 
  According to information reaching us from the government 
palace, the government was going to allow the citizens to 
participate tangibly in the management of the local affairs 
through the newly formed 10,000 district committees, which have 
been set up throughout the country over the past few months. 

</TEXT>

